Dialogue: 0,0:00:30.52,0:00:34.73,Default,,0,0,0,,[ Applause ]
Dialogue: 0,0:00:35.23,0:00:36.27,Default,,0,0,0,,>> My name is Mike Stern.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:36.46,0:00:38.06,Default,,0,0,0,,I manage the Design Evangelism
Dialogue: 0,0:00:38.06,0:00:39.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Team at Apple, and it is my
Dialogue: 0,0:00:39.84,0:00:41.51,Default,,0,0,0,,honor to be with you today to
Dialogue: 0,0:00:41.51,0:00:42.42,Default,,0,0,0,,talk about design.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:44.04,0:00:46.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, at Apple, we often use the
Dialogue: 0,0:00:46.23,0:00:48.97,Default,,0,0,0,,term human interface to describe
Dialogue: 0,0:00:48.97,0:00:50.55,Default,,0,0,0,,what might otherwise be called
Dialogue: 0,0:00:50.55,0:00:51.65,Default,,0,0,0,,user interface.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:52.33,0:00:55.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Human interface is an uncommon,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:55.57,0:00:58.06,Default,,0,0,0,,not widely used term, but it has
Dialogue: 0,0:00:58.06,0:01:01.18,Default,,0,0,0,,a really long history at Apple.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:01.18,0:01:02.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Our design documentation, this
Dialogue: 0,0:01:02.92,0:01:05.25,Default,,0,0,0,,is the newly redesigned macOS
Dialogue: 0,0:01:05.25,0:01:07.82,Default,,0,0,0,,HIG, it is called the Human
Dialogue: 0,0:01:07.82,0:01:09.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Interface Guidelines.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:10.80,0:01:12.89,Default,,0,0,0,,This document goes all the way
Dialogue: 0,0:01:12.89,0:01:17.04,Default,,0,0,0,,back to 1978, a full 15 years
Dialogue: 0,0:01:17.04,0:01:18.54,Default,,0,0,0,,before I was even born.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:19.30,0:01:19.76,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm just kidding.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:20.36,0:01:20.65,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm old [laughter].
Dialogue: 0,0:01:22.06,0:01:24.61,Default,,0,0,0,,The word user can have a
Dialogue: 0,0:01:24.72,0:01:27.13,Default,,0,0,0,,clinical or anonymizing effect.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:27.98,0:01:29.98,Default,,0,0,0,,It narrowly defines people in
Dialogue: 0,0:01:29.98,0:01:31.58,Default,,0,0,0,,relation to the interface.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:32.36,0:01:34.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Human evokes a much more nuance
Dialogue: 0,0:01:34.92,0:01:36.90,Default,,0,0,0,,picture of who it is that we are
Dialogue: 0,0:01:36.90,0:01:37.80,Default,,0,0,0,,designing for.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:38.52,0:01:40.13,Default,,0,0,0,,If I say I'm only human, it is
Dialogue: 0,0:01:40.19,0:01:41.79,Default,,0,0,0,,to acknowledge that I have
Dialogue: 0,0:01:41.79,0:01:43.91,Default,,0,0,0,,imperfections, and I have
Dialogue: 0,0:01:43.91,0:01:44.60,Default,,0,0,0,,shortcomings.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:44.60,0:01:45.85,Default,,0,0,0,,I might fall short of your
Dialogue: 0,0:01:45.85,0:01:47.00,Default,,0,0,0,,expectations of me.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:47.59,0:01:48.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Hopefully not right now.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:49.37,0:01:51.60,Default,,0,0,0,,But the word human is also how
Dialogue: 0,0:01:51.60,0:01:54.18,Default,,0,0,0,,we express our highest and most
Dialogue: 0,0:01:54.18,0:01:55.34,Default,,0,0,0,,noble qualities.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:56.10,0:01:57.19,Default,,0,0,0,,When you acknowledge someone's
Dialogue: 0,0:01:57.19,0:01:59.49,Default,,0,0,0,,humanity, you're recognizing
Dialogue: 0,0:01:59.83,0:02:01.40,Default,,0,0,0,,their kindness, their
Dialogue: 0,0:02:01.40,0:02:04.52,Default,,0,0,0,,compassion, their generosity and
Dialogue: 0,0:02:06.10,0:02:06.29,Default,,0,0,0,,goodness.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:06.43,0:02:08.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Designing an interface is
Dialogue: 0,0:02:08.16,0:02:09.78,Default,,0,0,0,,fundamentally about serving
Dialogue: 0,0:02:09.78,0:02:10.93,Default,,0,0,0,,other human beings.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:11.91,0:02:12.91,Default,,0,0,0,,The goal isn't to make a
Dialogue: 0,0:02:12.91,0:02:14.15,Default,,0,0,0,,beautiful app, or a
Dialogue: 0,0:02:14.15,0:02:16.48,Default,,0,0,0,,well-organized app, or a simple
Dialogue: 0,0:02:16.48,0:02:17.65,Default,,0,0,0,,app or a focused app.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:18.70,0:02:19.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Those things are all really
Dialogue: 0,0:02:19.92,0:02:21.56,Default,,0,0,0,,important, but they're not the
Dialogue: 0,0:02:21.67,0:02:22.41,Default,,0,0,0,,real goal.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:23.29,0:02:26.06,Default,,0,0,0,,The real goal is about serving
Dialogue: 0,0:02:26.15,0:02:28.25,Default,,0,0,0,,the human beings or positively
Dialogue: 0,0:02:28.32,0:02:29.93,Default,,0,0,0,,affecting the lives of the
Dialogue: 0,0:02:29.93,0:02:31.88,Default,,0,0,0,,people who use the apps that you
Dialogue: 0,0:02:31.88,0:02:32.21,Default,,0,0,0,,make.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:33.76,0:02:35.30,Default,,0,0,0,,The only thing that really
Dialogue: 0,0:02:35.30,0:02:37.13,Default,,0,0,0,,matters is how well your app
Dialogue: 0,0:02:37.52,0:02:39.59,Default,,0,0,0,,satisfies the emotional and
Dialogue: 0,0:02:39.59,0:02:41.72,Default,,0,0,0,,practical needs of the people
Dialogue: 0,0:02:41.72,0:02:42.79,Default,,0,0,0,,you are designing for.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:44.23,0:02:46.67,Default,,0,0,0,,We have the need for safety and
Dialogue: 0,0:02:46.67,0:02:47.62,Default,,0,0,0,,predictability.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:48.46,0:02:49.86,Default,,0,0,0,,We have a need for knowledge,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:50.13,0:02:52.28,Default,,0,0,0,,for meaning, and understanding.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:53.33,0:02:55.21,Default,,0,0,0,,We have a need to accomplish
Dialogue: 0,0:02:55.21,0:02:58.11,Default,,0,0,0,,tasks, to achieve our personal
Dialogue: 0,0:02:58.46,0:02:59.96,Default,,0,0,0,,and professional goals.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:00.99,0:03:02.45,Default,,0,0,0,,And we have the need to
Dialogue: 0,0:03:02.45,0:03:05.26,Default,,0,0,0,,experience beauty and joy.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:06.98,0:03:08.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Well-designed apps should
Dialogue: 0,0:03:08.95,0:03:10.18,Default,,0,0,0,,provide these things.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:11.28,0:03:13.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Well-designed apps make it easy
Dialogue: 0,0:03:13.26,0:03:15.05,Default,,0,0,0,,for people to predict the
Dialogue: 0,0:03:15.05,0:03:16.87,Default,,0,0,0,,consequences that their actions
Dialogue: 0,0:03:16.87,0:03:17.42,Default,,0,0,0,,will have.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:18.24,0:03:20.65,Default,,0,0,0,,They feel stable, solid,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:21.14,0:03:22.05,Default,,0,0,0,,trustworthy.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:23.28,0:03:24.35,Default,,0,0,0,,They help people to make
Dialogue: 0,0:03:24.35,0:03:26.47,Default,,0,0,0,,informed choices by providing
Dialogue: 0,0:03:26.47,0:03:28.33,Default,,0,0,0,,information that is clear and
Dialogue: 0,0:03:28.33,0:03:28.94,Default,,0,0,0,,helpful.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:29.85,0:03:31.08,Default,,0,0,0,,They have streamlined and
Dialogue: 0,0:03:31.08,0:03:33.51,Default,,0,0,0,,simplified workflows, so that
Dialogue: 0,0:03:33.51,0:03:35.24,Default,,0,0,0,,people can effectively and
Dialogue: 0,0:03:35.33,0:03:37.43,Default,,0,0,0,,efficiently accomplish their
Dialogue: 0,0:03:37.43,0:03:38.03,Default,,0,0,0,,tasks.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:38.64,0:03:40.56,Default,,0,0,0,,And they should have an
Dialogue: 0,0:03:40.97,0:03:42.52,Default,,0,0,0,,aesthetically pleasing,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:42.90,0:03:45.59,Default,,0,0,0,,enjoyable, and even delightful
Dialogue: 0,0:03:45.83,0:03:46.60,Default,,0,0,0,,experience.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:48.04,0:03:49.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Using apps that provides these
Dialogue: 0,0:03:49.52,0:03:51.98,Default,,0,0,0,,qualities is so gratifying, so
Dialogue: 0,0:03:52.05,0:03:53.80,Default,,0,0,0,,satisfying, you can tell that
Dialogue: 0,0:03:53.80,0:03:55.20,Default,,0,0,0,,the people who made the app
Dialogue: 0,0:03:55.95,0:03:58.46,Default,,0,0,0,,fully considered your needs.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:59.37,0:04:01.08,Default,,0,0,0,,You sense all the time and all
Dialogue: 0,0:04:01.08,0:04:02.01,Default,,0,0,0,,the effort that went into
Dialogue: 0,0:04:02.01,0:04:04.06,Default,,0,0,0,,figuring out how to help you get
Dialogue: 0,0:04:04.06,0:04:05.74,Default,,0,0,0,,things done quickly and
Dialogue: 0,0:04:05.74,0:04:06.51,Default,,0,0,0,,successfully.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:07.43,0:04:08.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Everything is there for a
Dialogue: 0,0:04:08.44,0:04:08.89,Default,,0,0,0,,purpose.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:09.58,0:04:11.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Everything is understandable.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:12.42,0:04:15.12,Default,,0,0,0,,It just feels so human.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:15.65,0:04:18.63,Default,,0,0,0,,When an app makes us feel this
Dialogue: 0,0:04:18.63,0:04:21.84,Default,,0,0,0,,way, we sense the humanity of
Dialogue: 0,0:04:21.84,0:04:23.40,Default,,0,0,0,,the people who designed it.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:24.56,0:04:26.51,Default,,0,0,0,,So how does the design of your
Dialogue: 0,0:04:26.51,0:04:28.40,Default,,0,0,0,,app accomplish this?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:28.86,0:04:30.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, when we talk about design,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:31.07,0:04:34.30,Default,,0,0,0,,we often focus on technique and
Dialogue: 0,0:04:34.30,0:04:34.95,Default,,0,0,0,,process.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:35.52,0:04:36.91,Default,,0,0,0,,And while these are important
Dialogue: 0,0:04:36.91,0:04:38.78,Default,,0,0,0,,considerations, they don't lead
Dialogue: 0,0:04:38.78,0:04:39.81,Default,,0,0,0,,to great designs.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:40.38,0:04:41.89,Default,,0,0,0,,At least not on their own.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:42.70,0:04:44.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Great designs are guided by a
Dialogue: 0,0:04:44.67,0:04:47.01,Default,,0,0,0,,deeper understanding about what
Dialogue: 0,0:04:47.01,0:04:49.26,Default,,0,0,0,,design is, at a more
Dialogue: 0,0:04:49.72,0:04:52.63,Default,,0,0,0,,fundamental, more human level.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:54.14,0:04:56.21,Default,,0,0,0,,This is what design principles
Dialogue: 0,0:04:56.21,0:04:57.10,Default,,0,0,0,,offer us.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:57.74,0:05:00.65,Default,,0,0,0,,They express core truths about
Dialogue: 0,0:05:00.65,0:05:02.45,Default,,0,0,0,,how we perceive the world around
Dialogue: 0,0:05:02.45,0:05:02.78,Default,,0,0,0,,us.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:03.40,0:05:05.64,Default,,0,0,0,,How we process information, how
Dialogue: 0,0:05:05.64,0:05:07.66,Default,,0,0,0,,we make decisions, and how we
Dialogue: 0,0:05:07.66,0:05:08.33,Default,,0,0,0,,communicate.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:09.34,0:05:12.40,Default,,0,0,0,,These truths are universal and
Dialogue: 0,0:05:12.40,0:05:13.05,Default,,0,0,0,,timeless.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:14.10,0:05:16.03,Default,,0,0,0,,They apply to all kinds of
Dialogue: 0,0:05:16.03,0:05:17.28,Default,,0,0,0,,graphic design.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:17.49,0:05:19.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Graphic design architecture,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:19.50,0:05:21.39,Default,,0,0,0,,interior design, retail design,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:21.39,0:05:22.51,Default,,0,0,0,,landscape design, landscape
Dialogue: 0,0:05:22.51,0:05:24.20,Default,,0,0,0,,design, automotive design, I
Dialogue: 0,0:05:24.42,0:05:25.49,Default,,0,0,0,,think I said landscape twice,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:26.12,0:05:27.71,Default,,0,0,0,,and every other type of design.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:29.06,0:05:30.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Design principles don't tell us
Dialogue: 0,0:05:31.06,0:05:33.36,Default,,0,0,0,,how to do specific things in our
Dialogue: 0,0:05:33.36,0:05:35.97,Default,,0,0,0,,design, they tell us why we
Dialogue: 0,0:05:35.97,0:05:37.07,Default,,0,0,0,,should do those things.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:38.27,0:05:40.08,Default,,0,0,0,,They serve as the foundation
Dialogue: 0,0:05:40.21,0:05:42.96,Default,,0,0,0,,upon which great designs are
Dialogue: 0,0:05:42.96,0:05:43.24,Default,,0,0,0,,built.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:44.27,0:05:46.53,Default,,0,0,0,,This session is about sharing
Dialogue: 0,0:05:46.78,0:05:48.58,Default,,0,0,0,,those principles with you.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:49.77,0:05:52.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, some of the things I'll
Dialogue: 0,0:05:52.28,0:05:54.23,Default,,0,0,0,,share today might seem kind of
Dialogue: 0,0:05:54.73,0:05:56.22,Default,,0,0,0,,basic or obvious.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:57.32,0:05:59.80,Default,,0,0,0,,But the most profound things are
Dialogue: 0,0:05:59.80,0:06:00.90,Default,,0,0,0,,often the simplest.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:01.71,0:06:03.46,Default,,0,0,0,,I've been designing for over 20
Dialogue: 0,0:06:03.46,0:06:03.94,Default,,0,0,0,,years.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:04.41,0:06:05.67,Default,,0,0,0,,I've been fortunate enough to
Dialogue: 0,0:06:05.67,0:06:06.77,Default,,0,0,0,,have worked with many brilliant
Dialogue: 0,0:06:06.77,0:06:08.73,Default,,0,0,0,,designers, both at Apple and in
Dialogue: 0,0:06:08.73,0:06:09.78,Default,,0,0,0,,the developer community.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:10.54,0:06:12.07,Default,,0,0,0,,I've had in-depth discussions
Dialogue: 0,0:06:12.07,0:06:13.17,Default,,0,0,0,,about a wide range of
Dialogue: 0,0:06:13.17,0:06:14.83,Default,,0,0,0,,interaction design challenges
Dialogue: 0,0:06:15.50,0:06:17.68,Default,,0,0,0,,across a full spectrum of apps
Dialogue: 0,0:06:17.68,0:06:19.32,Default,,0,0,0,,and games with people from
Dialogue: 0,0:06:19.32,0:06:20.18,Default,,0,0,0,,across the globe.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:21.08,0:06:22.85,Default,,0,0,0,,And in all of those experiences,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:22.85,0:06:24.67,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm constantly reminded, I
Dialogue: 0,0:06:24.67,0:06:26.93,Default,,0,0,0,,constantly return to just how
Dialogue: 0,0:06:26.93,0:06:29.36,Default,,0,0,0,,clarifying it is to evaluate a
Dialogue: 0,0:06:29.36,0:06:31.41,Default,,0,0,0,,design against the core
Dialogue: 0,0:06:31.41,0:06:33.40,Default,,0,0,0,,principles that we are about to
Dialogue: 0,0:06:33.40,0:06:33.83,Default,,0,0,0,,explore.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:35.63,0:06:38.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay. So, because design
Dialogue: 0,0:06:38.95,0:06:41.07,Default,,0,0,0,,principles are universal, I
Dialogue: 0,0:06:41.07,0:06:42.25,Default,,0,0,0,,thought it would be fun for us
Dialogue: 0,0:06:42.25,0:06:43.97,Default,,0,0,0,,to explore how these design
Dialogue: 0,0:06:43.97,0:06:46.44,Default,,0,0,0,,principles shape our experiences
Dialogue: 0,0:06:46.90,0:06:48.41,Default,,0,0,0,,in the real world.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:49.18,0:06:50.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, there really is no better
Dialogue: 0,0:06:50.86,0:06:52.52,Default,,0,0,0,,way to explore the real world
Dialogue: 0,0:06:52.52,0:06:53.28,Default,,0,0,0,,than to travel.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:53.91,0:06:55.44,Default,,0,0,0,,So, with that in mind, I thought
Dialogue: 0,0:06:55.44,0:06:57.22,Default,,0,0,0,,we would all go on a little trip
Dialogue: 0,0:06:57.22,0:06:57.57,Default,,0,0,0,,together.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:58.61,0:07:00.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, it took quite a bit of
Dialogue: 0,0:07:00.05,0:07:02.60,Default,,0,0,0,,persuading, but we managed to
Dialogue: 0,0:07:02.60,0:07:04.13,Default,,0,0,0,,allocate a portion of the
Dialogue: 0,0:07:04.13,0:07:06.29,Default,,0,0,0,,evangelism team's travel budget
Dialogue: 0,0:07:06.65,0:07:08.37,Default,,0,0,0,,to buy each one of you here
Dialogue: 0,0:07:08.37,0:07:11.19,Default,,0,0,0,,today a ticket to Hawaii.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:12.37,0:07:13.83,Default,,0,0,0,,What? Right?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:14.44,0:07:15.36,Default,,0,0,0,,That's pretty awesome.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:16.73,0:07:18.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Sandy beaches, rainforests,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:18.77,0:07:19.78,Default,,0,0,0,,tropical drinks.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:20.38,0:07:21.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Sounds pretty great, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:22.66,0:07:23.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay who is down?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:23.29,0:07:23.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Who wants to go on this trip?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:24.21,0:07:25.21,Default,,0,0,0,,[Applause and cheering] Yeah?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:25.48,0:07:27.55,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:28.10,0:07:30.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's go. Now, our journey to
Dialogue: 0,0:07:30.24,0:07:31.86,Default,,0,0,0,,lovely Hawaii is going to begin
Dialogue: 0,0:07:31.86,0:07:33.73,Default,,0,0,0,,somewhere slightly less lovely,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:34.35,0:07:35.06,Default,,0,0,0,,at the airport.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:36.15,0:07:37.63,Default,,0,0,0,,As we approach the airport, we
Dialogue: 0,0:07:37.63,0:07:39.24,Default,,0,0,0,,are going to see all sorts of
Dialogue: 0,0:07:39.24,0:07:39.91,Default,,0,0,0,,signs.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:41.01,0:07:42.66,Default,,0,0,0,,At first, we see signs about how
Dialogue: 0,0:07:42.66,0:07:44.10,Default,,0,0,0,,to get to our terminal.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:44.89,0:07:47.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Then we see signs that provide
Dialogue: 0,0:07:47.22,0:07:48.71,Default,,0,0,0,,more specific information about
Dialogue: 0,0:07:48.71,0:07:49.92,Default,,0,0,0,,what's at each terminal, and
Dialogue: 0,0:07:50.21,0:07:51.89,Default,,0,0,0,,after we find our terminal and
Dialogue: 0,0:07:51.93,0:07:54.10,Default,,0,0,0,,park, we head into the terminal,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:54.10,0:07:55.95,Default,,0,0,0,,and then we get directions to
Dialogue: 0,0:07:55.95,0:07:56.45,Default,,0,0,0,,our gate.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:57.09,0:07:58.43,Default,,0,0,0,,And once we get to our gate, we
Dialogue: 0,0:07:58.43,0:07:59.23,Default,,0,0,0,,are going to know we're in the
Dialogue: 0,0:07:59.23,0:08:00.83,Default,,0,0,0,,right place, because there is a
Dialogue: 0,0:08:00.83,0:08:02.74,Default,,0,0,0,,big old sign telling us so.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:03.57,0:08:04.44,Default,,0,0,0,,And if we are in the wrong
Dialogue: 0,0:08:04.44,0:08:05.88,Default,,0,0,0,,place, or if our flight was
Dialogue: 0,0:08:05.88,0:08:08.49,Default,,0,0,0,,moved, we get directions to
Dialogue: 0,0:08:08.49,0:08:09.40,Default,,0,0,0,,nearby gates.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:10.55,0:08:11.80,Default,,0,0,0,,And in case there is an
Dialogue: 0,0:08:11.80,0:08:14.03,Default,,0,0,0,,emergency or we just want to
Dialogue: 0,0:08:14.03,0:08:16.42,Default,,0,0,0,,leave, nearby exits are clearly
Dialogue: 0,0:08:16.42,0:08:16.72,Default,,0,0,0,,marked.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:18.17,0:08:19.65,Default,,0,0,0,,The system of signs that we
Dialogue: 0,0:08:19.65,0:08:21.45,Default,,0,0,0,,followed is what is called a
Dialogue: 0,0:08:21.45,0:08:22.61,Default,,0,0,0,,wayfinding system.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:23.39,0:08:25.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Wayfinding systems help people
Dialogue: 0,0:08:25.75,0:08:27.94,Default,,0,0,0,,to navigate complex environments
Dialogue: 0,0:08:28.26,0:08:29.62,Default,,0,0,0,,quickly and successfully.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:30.29,0:08:31.49,Default,,0,0,0,,They are critical for helping
Dialogue: 0,0:08:31.49,0:08:33.82,Default,,0,0,0,,people feel oriented and safe.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:34.67,0:08:36.74,Default,,0,0,0,,People at airports are tired,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:36.82,0:08:38.79,Default,,0,0,0,,they're jet-lagged, they're in a
Dialogue: 0,0:08:38.79,0:08:40.40,Default,,0,0,0,,rush, they're stressed out.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:41.07,0:08:42.54,Default,,0,0,0,,So airports need to think really
Dialogue: 0,0:08:42.54,0:08:44.24,Default,,0,0,0,,deeply about wayfinding.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:44.94,0:08:48.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Good wayfinding systems offer a
Dialogue: 0,0:08:48.07,0:08:50.10,Default,,0,0,0,,comprehensive and understandable
Dialogue: 0,0:08:50.10,0:08:53.16,Default,,0,0,0,,list of general locations that
Dialogue: 0,0:08:53.16,0:08:54.19,Default,,0,0,0,,people can visit.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:55.14,0:08:57.12,Default,,0,0,0,,They provide needed detail about
Dialogue: 0,0:08:57.12,0:08:58.50,Default,,0,0,0,,what's in those locations.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:59.63,0:09:01.13,Default,,0,0,0,,They are highly contextual.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:01.68,0:09:02.84,Default,,0,0,0,,They become increasingly
Dialogue: 0,0:09:02.84,0:09:04.94,Default,,0,0,0,,specific as we navigate deeper
Dialogue: 0,0:09:04.94,0:09:06.26,Default,,0,0,0,,and deeper into the system.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:07.11,0:09:08.44,Default,,0,0,0,,They help people to orient
Dialogue: 0,0:09:08.44,0:09:09.80,Default,,0,0,0,,themselves by clearly
Dialogue: 0,0:09:09.80,0:09:10.82,Default,,0,0,0,,highlighting their current
Dialogue: 0,0:09:10.82,0:09:12.65,Default,,0,0,0,,location relative to other
Dialogue: 0,0:09:12.65,0:09:13.47,Default,,0,0,0,,locations.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:14.10,0:09:16.49,Default,,0,0,0,,And they provide a clear exit
Dialogue: 0,0:09:16.49,0:09:16.63,Default,,0,0,0,,path.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:17.82,0:09:20.01,Default,,0,0,0,,It's so comforting to know that
Dialogue: 0,0:09:20.01,0:09:21.91,Default,,0,0,0,,you can return to a place that
Dialogue: 0,0:09:21.91,0:09:24.00,Default,,0,0,0,,is more familiar and start over.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:25.10,0:09:28.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Wayfinding helps us to feel safe
Dialogue: 0,0:09:28.35,0:09:30.23,Default,,0,0,0,,by answering really basic
Dialogue: 0,0:09:30.23,0:09:33.14,Default,,0,0,0,,questions like: where am I?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:34.25,0:09:35.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Where can I go?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:36.08,0:09:37.58,Default,,0,0,0,,What will I find when I get
Dialogue: 0,0:09:37.58,0:09:37.86,Default,,0,0,0,,there?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:38.93,0:09:39.62,Default,,0,0,0,,What's nearby?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:40.58,0:09:41.87,Default,,0,0,0,,And how do I get out?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:43.07,0:09:44.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Without answers to questions
Dialogue: 0,0:09:44.63,0:09:46.40,Default,,0,0,0,,like these, we'd be lost.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:47.27,0:09:49.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, your app's interface is
Dialogue: 0,0:09:49.37,0:09:51.07,Default,,0,0,0,,really just one big old
Dialogue: 0,0:09:51.07,0:09:52.19,Default,,0,0,0,,wayfinding system.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:52.72,0:09:54.18,Default,,0,0,0,,The navigation bar, the content
Dialogue: 0,0:09:54.18,0:09:55.45,Default,,0,0,0,,area, the tab bar, they're all
Dialogue: 0,0:09:55.45,0:09:56.64,Default,,0,0,0,,just tools for providing
Dialogue: 0,0:09:56.64,0:09:58.19,Default,,0,0,0,,wayfinding in your app.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:58.81,0:10:00.37,Default,,0,0,0,,The navigation bar title and
Dialogue: 0,0:10:00.37,0:10:02.11,Default,,0,0,0,,selected tab bar item lets
Dialogue: 0,0:10:02.11,0:10:02.97,Default,,0,0,0,,people know where they are.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:04.29,0:10:06.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Tab bar in content areas lets
Dialogue: 0,0:10:06.06,0:10:07.28,Default,,0,0,0,,people know where they can go
Dialogue: 0,0:10:07.28,0:10:08.06,Default,,0,0,0,,and what's nearby.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:09.04,0:10:11.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Simply rendered and recognizable
Dialogue: 0,0:10:11.06,0:10:12.33,Default,,0,0,0,,tab bar glyphs and
Dialogue: 0,0:10:12.33,0:10:14.97,Default,,0,0,0,,understandable labels suggest to
Dialogue: 0,0:10:14.97,0:10:16.72,Default,,0,0,0,,people what they will find when
Dialogue: 0,0:10:16.72,0:10:17.29,Default,,0,0,0,,they get there.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:18.58,0:10:20.78,Default,,0,0,0,,And back buttons offer an exit
Dialogue: 0,0:10:20.85,0:10:21.91,Default,,0,0,0,,route, and can help people to
Dialogue: 0,0:10:21.91,0:10:23.65,Default,,0,0,0,,identify what area of the app
Dialogue: 0,0:10:23.72,0:10:24.21,Default,,0,0,0,,that they're in.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:25.57,0:10:27.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Now every screen in your app
Dialogue: 0,0:10:28.33,0:10:29.79,Default,,0,0,0,,should answer all of these
Dialogue: 0,0:10:29.79,0:10:31.49,Default,,0,0,0,,questions, or else people will
Dialogue: 0,0:10:31.49,0:10:32.29,Default,,0,0,0,,feel lost.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:32.83,0:10:35.18,Default,,0,0,0,,So go through your app.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:35.94,0:10:37.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Go one screen at a time, and ask
Dialogue: 0,0:10:37.84,0:10:39.31,Default,,0,0,0,,yourself, how well is each
Dialogue: 0,0:10:39.31,0:10:40.51,Default,,0,0,0,,screen answering these
Dialogue: 0,0:10:40.51,0:10:41.03,Default,,0,0,0,,questions?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:42.11,0:10:43.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Does every screen help people to
Dialogue: 0,0:10:43.81,0:10:44.65,Default,,0,0,0,,know where they are?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:45.26,0:10:46.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Does every screen help provide
Dialogue: 0,0:10:46.86,0:10:48.85,Default,,0,0,0,,options to people to tell them
Dialogue: 0,0:10:48.85,0:10:49.77,Default,,0,0,0,,where else they can go?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:50.37,0:10:52.41,Default,,0,0,0,,If some screens aren't answering
Dialogue: 0,0:10:52.41,0:10:54.66,Default,,0,0,0,,those questions clearly, then
Dialogue: 0,0:10:54.66,0:10:55.97,Default,,0,0,0,,there is some work to be done.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:55.97,0:10:57.65,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:58.07,0:11:00.37,Default,,0,0,0,,So we have a flight to catch.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:00.78,0:11:01.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Paradise awaits.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:03.10,0:11:04.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Wow. That was a quick flight.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:04.70,0:11:07.06,Default,,0,0,0,,If only they were all so quick.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:08.49,0:11:10.51,Default,,0,0,0,,So we have arrived in paradise,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:10.75,0:11:12.56,Default,,0,0,0,,and it's time to pick up our car
Dialogue: 0,0:11:12.56,0:11:13.68,Default,,0,0,0,,and head to the hotel.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:14.47,0:11:16.26,Default,,0,0,0,,What a sweet car it is.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:16.42,0:11:18.39,Default,,0,0,0,,It has got a sweet candy red
Dialogue: 0,0:11:18.39,0:11:19.15,Default,,0,0,0,,paint job.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:19.46,0:11:20.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Check out those rims.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:21.00,0:11:22.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Looks like it will do zero to 60
Dialogue: 0,0:11:22.61,0:11:25.80,Default,,0,0,0,,in like 10 or maybe 11 seconds.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:26.56,0:11:27.75,Default,,0,0,0,,It is a pretty small car.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:27.75,0:11:29.23,Default,,0,0,0,,If I were you, I would yell out
Dialogue: 0,0:11:29.23,0:11:30.42,Default,,0,0,0,,shotgun right now.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:31.86,0:11:32.60,Default,,0,0,0,,>> Shotgun!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:32.60,0:11:33.94,Default,,0,0,0,,>> [Laughs] All right, all
Dialogue: 0,0:11:33.94,0:11:36.09,Default,,0,0,0,,joking aside, cars are actually
Dialogue: 0,0:11:36.09,0:11:36.96,Default,,0,0,0,,quite dangerous.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:37.43,0:11:38.72,Default,,0,0,0,,The fact that we let people
Dialogue: 0,0:11:38.72,0:11:40.08,Default,,0,0,0,,drive around two-ton metal
Dialogue: 0,0:11:40.08,0:11:41.74,Default,,0,0,0,,objects at high velocities is
Dialogue: 0,0:11:41.74,0:11:42.80,Default,,0,0,0,,kind of ludicrous.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:43.25,0:11:44.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Especially when those people
Dialogue: 0,0:11:44.87,0:11:46.88,Default,,0,0,0,,could be tired and navigating
Dialogue: 0,0:11:46.88,0:11:48.06,Default,,0,0,0,,unfamiliar roads.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:48.91,0:11:50.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, because of the inherent
Dialogue: 0,0:11:50.39,0:11:52.99,Default,,0,0,0,,danger of driving a vehicle, car
Dialogue: 0,0:11:52.99,0:11:54.33,Default,,0,0,0,,manufacturers have to think
Dialogue: 0,0:11:54.62,0:11:56.34,Default,,0,0,0,,carefully about the design of
Dialogue: 0,0:11:56.34,0:11:57.01,Default,,0,0,0,,interiors.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:57.01,0:11:58.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Safety is a primary
Dialogue: 0,0:11:58.92,0:11:59.80,Default,,0,0,0,,consideration.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:00.38,0:12:02.00,Default,,0,0,0,,And so they're a great way for
Dialogue: 0,0:12:02.00,0:12:03.40,Default,,0,0,0,,us to learn about the design
Dialogue: 0,0:12:03.40,0:12:04.97,Default,,0,0,0,,principle of feedback.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:06.30,0:12:08.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Feedback helps us to operate
Dialogue: 0,0:12:08.15,0:12:10.36,Default,,0,0,0,,cars confidently and safely.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:10.89,0:12:12.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Feedback helps us to anticipate
Dialogue: 0,0:12:12.89,0:12:14.78,Default,,0,0,0,,problems that might cause the
Dialogue: 0,0:12:14.78,0:12:16.76,Default,,0,0,0,,car to stop functioning properly
Dialogue: 0,0:12:16.76,0:12:18.54,Default,,0,0,0,,or to stop moving all together.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:19.39,0:12:21.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Our vacation definitely won't be
Dialogue: 0,0:12:21.47,0:12:23.19,Default,,0,0,0,,very fun if that happens.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:24.09,0:12:25.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, cars provide various forms
Dialogue: 0,0:12:25.71,0:12:26.13,Default,,0,0,0,,of feedback.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:26.66,0:12:28.04,Default,,0,0,0,,There is status feedback to let
Dialogue: 0,0:12:28.04,0:12:29.54,Default,,0,0,0,,us know how the car is doing.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:29.99,0:12:31.35,Default,,0,0,0,,There is completion feedback to
Dialogue: 0,0:12:31.35,0:12:33.53,Default,,0,0,0,,let us know whether actions
Dialogue: 0,0:12:33.53,0:12:34.72,Default,,0,0,0,,we've performed are completed
Dialogue: 0,0:12:35.06,0:12:36.46,Default,,0,0,0,,successfully or failed.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:37.12,0:12:38.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Warning feedback, to tell us
Dialogue: 0,0:12:38.59,0:12:39.91,Default,,0,0,0,,about potential problems.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:40.51,0:12:41.78,Default,,0,0,0,,And there is feedback to let us
Dialogue: 0,0:12:41.78,0:12:43.14,Default,,0,0,0,,know when something we've tried
Dialogue: 0,0:12:43.14,0:12:45.04,Default,,0,0,0,,to do has caused an error.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:45.60,0:12:48.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, for our safety, for the
Dialogue: 0,0:12:48.51,0:12:49.84,Default,,0,0,0,,safety of other drivers and
Dialogue: 0,0:12:49.84,0:12:51.88,Default,,0,0,0,,pedestrians, the feedback that
Dialogue: 0,0:12:51.88,0:12:53.57,Default,,0,0,0,,cars provide must be clear,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:54.00,0:12:55.99,Default,,0,0,0,,immediate, and understandable.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:56.90,0:12:58.70,Default,,0,0,0,,So let's check out how cars
Dialogue: 0,0:12:58.70,0:13:01.01,Default,,0,0,0,,communicate with us, starting
Dialogue: 0,0:13:01.01,0:13:02.20,Default,,0,0,0,,with how they tell us about
Dialogue: 0,0:13:02.20,0:13:02.98,Default,,0,0,0,,their status.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:03.84,0:13:05.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, we have all loaded into the
Dialogue: 0,0:13:05.14,0:13:07.04,Default,,0,0,0,,car, and we are ready to go.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:07.74,0:13:09.81,Default,,0,0,0,,So looking at the gear shifter,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:10.10,0:13:11.68,Default,,0,0,0,,I can see that the car is in
Dialogue: 0,0:13:11.68,0:13:12.08,Default,,0,0,0,,park.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:12.82,0:13:14.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Knowing what gear the car is in
Dialogue: 0,0:13:14.93,0:13:16.85,Default,,0,0,0,,is super important information.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:17.39,0:13:18.79,Default,,0,0,0,,It is so important that it's
Dialogue: 0,0:13:18.84,0:13:20.73,Default,,0,0,0,,displayed twice, on the
Dialogue: 0,0:13:20.73,0:13:22.76,Default,,0,0,0,,gearshift, and in the instrument
Dialogue: 0,0:13:22.76,0:13:23.21,Default,,0,0,0,,cluster.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:23.99,0:13:25.48,Default,,0,0,0,,It would be really bad if I
Dialogue: 0,0:13:25.48,0:13:27.16,Default,,0,0,0,,thought the car was in park when
Dialogue: 0,0:13:27.16,0:13:29.60,Default,,0,0,0,,it was actually in drive, or if
Dialogue: 0,0:13:29.60,0:13:30.91,Default,,0,0,0,,I thought the car was in drive,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:30.95,0:13:32.76,Default,,0,0,0,,when it was actually in reverse.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:33.82,0:13:35.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Other status feedback lets me
Dialogue: 0,0:13:35.40,0:13:36.86,Default,,0,0,0,,see the fuel level, so I can
Dialogue: 0,0:13:36.86,0:13:38.99,Default,,0,0,0,,anticipate and predict how far
Dialogue: 0,0:13:38.99,0:13:40.52,Default,,0,0,0,,we can go before we need to
Dialogue: 0,0:13:40.52,0:13:41.08,Default,,0,0,0,,refuel.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:42.26,0:13:43.69,Default,,0,0,0,,And seeing our current speed
Dialogue: 0,0:13:43.69,0:13:45.88,Default,,0,0,0,,helps me to avoid getting costly
Dialogue: 0,0:13:45.88,0:13:46.79,Default,,0,0,0,,speeding tickets.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:47.63,0:13:49.08,Default,,0,0,0,,These are two really critical
Dialogue: 0,0:13:49.08,0:13:50.23,Default,,0,0,0,,pieces of information.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:50.53,0:13:51.60,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't want to run out of gas
Dialogue: 0,0:13:51.60,0:13:53.30,Default,,0,0,0,,before we get to the hotel, and
Dialogue: 0,0:13:53.30,0:13:54.59,Default,,0,0,0,,the lovely folks in finance have
Dialogue: 0,0:13:54.59,0:13:56.61,Default,,0,0,0,,told me repeatedly that I cannot
Dialogue: 0,0:13:56.96,0:13:58.19,Default,,0,0,0,,expend speeding tickets.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:59.01,0:14:00.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, status information in apps
Dialogue: 0,0:14:00.84,0:14:02.28,Default,,0,0,0,,should be just as clear.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:02.87,0:14:04.43,Default,,0,0,0,,So, for example, in the mail
Dialogue: 0,0:14:04.67,0:14:06.39,Default,,0,0,0,,app, unread status indicators
Dialogue: 0,0:14:06.77,0:14:09.22,Default,,0,0,0,,help people to prioritize which
Dialogue: 0,0:14:09.22,0:14:10.86,Default,,0,0,0,,emails to read first.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:11.63,0:14:13.43,Default,,0,0,0,,In Calendar, status indicators
Dialogue: 0,0:14:13.43,0:14:15.22,Default,,0,0,0,,help people to see when someone
Dialogue: 0,0:14:15.22,0:14:16.08,Default,,0,0,0,,can't make a meeting and it
Dialogue: 0,0:14:16.08,0:14:17.18,Default,,0,0,0,,helps them determine if they
Dialogue: 0,0:14:17.18,0:14:18.13,Default,,0,0,0,,need to reschedule.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:19.11,0:14:20.26,Default,,0,0,0,,In the Camera app, there are
Dialogue: 0,0:14:20.42,0:14:22.10,Default,,0,0,0,,three elements to let people
Dialogue: 0,0:14:22.10,0:14:23.37,Default,,0,0,0,,know that a video is being
Dialogue: 0,0:14:23.37,0:14:23.93,Default,,0,0,0,,recorded.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:24.38,0:14:26.04,Default,,0,0,0,,The red dot, the incrementing
Dialogue: 0,0:14:26.04,0:14:27.51,Default,,0,0,0,,time code, the state of the
Dialogue: 0,0:14:27.51,0:14:28.36,Default,,0,0,0,,record button.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:28.88,0:14:30.92,Default,,0,0,0,,They all let people know that a
Dialogue: 0,0:14:30.92,0:14:33.64,Default,,0,0,0,,precious but fleeing moment is
Dialogue: 0,0:14:33.64,0:14:34.49,Default,,0,0,0,,being recorded.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:35.78,0:14:37.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Showing status clearly and
Dialogue: 0,0:14:37.68,0:14:40.20,Default,,0,0,0,,directly is crucial for saving
Dialogue: 0,0:14:40.20,0:14:42.41,Default,,0,0,0,,people time and helping them to
Dialogue: 0,0:14:42.41,0:14:43.79,Default,,0,0,0,,avoid making mistakes.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:44.95,0:14:46.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Next up is completion feedback.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:46.94,0:14:49.01,Default,,0,0,0,,We are ready to go, so I start
Dialogue: 0,0:14:49.01,0:14:49.41,Default,,0,0,0,,the car [engine starts].
Dialogue: 0,0:14:50.69,0:14:53.84,Default,,0,0,0,,We can hear the engine turn
Dialogue: 0,0:14:53.84,0:14:54.14,Default,,0,0,0,,over.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:54.51,0:14:56.58,Default,,0,0,0,,We can feel the vibration of the
Dialogue: 0,0:14:56.58,0:14:57.26,Default,,0,0,0,,motor running.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:57.91,0:15:00.04,Default,,0,0,0,,We see that instrument cluster
Dialogue: 0,0:15:00.16,0:15:00.99,Default,,0,0,0,,come to life.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:01.92,0:15:03.32,Default,,0,0,0,,There is no doubt that we are
Dialogue: 0,0:15:03.32,0:15:04.07,Default,,0,0,0,,ready to go.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:04.96,0:15:07.56,Default,,0,0,0,,And as I shift, from Park into
Dialogue: 0,0:15:07.56,0:15:11.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Drive, I get tactile feedback to
Dialogue: 0,0:15:11.13,0:15:12.44,Default,,0,0,0,,let me know that I'm moving
Dialogue: 0,0:15:12.44,0:15:13.45,Default,,0,0,0,,through those gears.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:14.48,0:15:15.47,Default,,0,0,0,,And as we pull out of the
Dialogue: 0,0:15:15.47,0:15:17.33,Default,,0,0,0,,parking spot, we hear [clicking]
Dialogue: 0,0:15:18.04,0:15:19.25,Default,,0,0,0,,the doors lock.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:20.15,0:15:21.85,Default,,0,0,0,,This happens automatically, so
Dialogue: 0,0:15:21.85,0:15:23.59,Default,,0,0,0,,it is even more important that
Dialogue: 0,0:15:23.59,0:15:24.63,Default,,0,0,0,,we get this feedback.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:25.45,0:15:26.92,Default,,0,0,0,,All of this feedback is
Dialogue: 0,0:15:26.92,0:15:27.70,Default,,0,0,0,,reassuring.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:28.28,0:15:30.12,Default,,0,0,0,,It's our car's way of saying it
Dialogue: 0,0:15:30.12,0:15:32.21,Default,,0,0,0,,is all good, I'm doing exactly
Dialogue: 0,0:15:32.21,0:15:33.79,Default,,0,0,0,,what it is that you wanted me to
Dialogue: 0,0:15:33.79,0:15:35.82,Default,,0,0,0,,do, and this frees me up to
Dialogue: 0,0:15:35.91,0:15:37.95,Default,,0,0,0,,focus on other cognitive tasks,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:37.95,0:15:39.96,Default,,0,0,0,,like making sure it's safe to
Dialogue: 0,0:15:39.96,0:15:41.29,Default,,0,0,0,,pull out of the parking spot.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:42.32,0:15:43.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Completion feedback in apps
Dialogue: 0,0:15:44.21,0:15:45.78,Default,,0,0,0,,serves the very same purpose.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:46.70,0:15:48.14,Default,,0,0,0,,The sound of a locked iPhone
Dialogue: 0,0:15:48.14,0:15:48.70,Default,,0,0,0,,[clicking].
Dialogue: 0,0:15:48.70,0:15:51.85,Default,,0,0,0,,The animation of an email being
Dialogue: 0,0:15:51.85,0:15:54.61,Default,,0,0,0,,marked as unread, or the
Dialogue: 0,0:15:54.61,0:15:56.34,Default,,0,0,0,,animation of an email being
Dialogue: 0,0:15:56.34,0:15:56.76,Default,,0,0,0,,deleted.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:57.79,0:15:59.33,Default,,0,0,0,,These cues are discreet, and
Dialogue: 0,0:15:59.33,0:16:00.54,Default,,0,0,0,,they're non-invasive, but
Dialogue: 0,0:16:00.80,0:16:02.14,Default,,0,0,0,,they're hard to ignore, and they
Dialogue: 0,0:16:02.14,0:16:03.23,Default,,0,0,0,,provide that necessary
Dialogue: 0,0:16:03.23,0:16:05.21,Default,,0,0,0,,reassurance that our devices are
Dialogue: 0,0:16:05.21,0:16:06.76,Default,,0,0,0,,performing as expected.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:07.64,0:16:09.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Of course, confirmation feedback
Dialogue: 0,0:16:09.72,0:16:11.37,Default,,0,0,0,,can be even more obvious.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:11.95,0:16:13.10,Default,,0,0,0,,The animation and sound of a
Dialogue: 0,0:16:13.10,0:16:14.97,Default,,0,0,0,,successful Apple Pay transaction
Dialogue: 0,0:16:14.97,0:16:15.32,Default,,0,0,0,,[tone sounds].
Dialogue: 0,0:16:15.32,0:16:17.49,Default,,0,0,0,,It's very hard to miss.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:18.10,0:16:20.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Every action taken in your app
Dialogue: 0,0:16:21.19,0:16:22.64,Default,,0,0,0,,should provide some form of
Dialogue: 0,0:16:22.64,0:16:24.38,Default,,0,0,0,,confirmation feedback, because
Dialogue: 0,0:16:24.38,0:16:25.90,Default,,0,0,0,,it is absolutely necessary for
Dialogue: 0,0:16:25.90,0:16:27.32,Default,,0,0,0,,letting people know that actions
Dialogue: 0,0:16:27.32,0:16:28.69,Default,,0,0,0,,they've performed were
Dialogue: 0,0:16:28.69,0:16:29.33,Default,,0,0,0,,successful.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:30.55,0:16:32.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Warnings help people to
Dialogue: 0,0:16:32.04,0:16:33.42,Default,,0,0,0,,understand in advance about
Dialogue: 0,0:16:33.42,0:16:34.37,Default,,0,0,0,,potential errors.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:35.02,0:16:36.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Low fuel level.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:36.59,0:16:37.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Low break pads.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:38.07,0:16:39.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Low oil level.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:40.28,0:16:41.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Warnings can be communicated
Dialogue: 0,0:16:41.71,0:16:43.13,Default,,0,0,0,,using status indicators,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:43.13,0:16:44.82,Default,,0,0,0,,messages, and the instrument
Dialogue: 0,0:16:44.82,0:16:46.21,Default,,0,0,0,,cluster, built-in display,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:46.53,0:16:48.43,Default,,0,0,0,,sounds, or all of the above.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:49.31,0:16:50.96,Default,,0,0,0,,These warnings are important.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:51.26,0:16:52.77,Default,,0,0,0,,They keep us safe, and they
Dialogue: 0,0:16:53.04,0:16:55.11,Default,,0,0,0,,protect our car from damage.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:56.06,0:16:58.25,Default,,0,0,0,,And lastly, error feedback in
Dialogue: 0,0:16:58.25,0:17:01.00,Default,,0,0,0,,cars, as with apps, is crucial.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:01.94,0:17:03.14,Default,,0,0,0,,If you try to start a car
Dialogue: 0,0:17:03.14,0:17:05.09,Default,,0,0,0,,without gas, you will get an
Dialogue: 0,0:17:05.09,0:17:06.33,Default,,0,0,0,,error message about that.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:07.16,0:17:08.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Now errors are always
Dialogue: 0,0:17:09.17,0:17:10.85,Default,,0,0,0,,disappointing and frustrating.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:11.32,0:17:12.97,Default,,0,0,0,,It's best to help people avoid
Dialogue: 0,0:17:12.97,0:17:14.14,Default,,0,0,0,,making errors in the first
Dialogue: 0,0:17:14.14,0:17:14.56,Default,,0,0,0,,place.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:15.26,0:17:17.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Warnings and confirmation
Dialogue: 0,0:17:17.07,0:17:17.93,Default,,0,0,0,,feedback can help.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:18.73,0:17:20.32,Default,,0,0,0,,For instance, in-line form
Dialogue: 0,0:17:20.32,0:17:21.69,Default,,0,0,0,,validation is a fantastic
Dialogue: 0,0:17:21.72,0:17:23.20,Default,,0,0,0,,technique for letting people
Dialogue: 0,0:17:23.20,0:17:24.45,Default,,0,0,0,,know what values will be
Dialogue: 0,0:17:24.45,0:17:27.12,Default,,0,0,0,,accepted, and what values will
Dialogue: 0,0:17:27.12,0:17:27.35,Default,,0,0,0,,not.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:28.74,0:17:29.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Getting this feedback in real
Dialogue: 0,0:17:29.85,0:17:31.71,Default,,0,0,0,,time helps people to course
Dialogue: 0,0:17:31.71,0:17:32.99,Default,,0,0,0,,correct so that they don't run
Dialogue: 0,0:17:32.99,0:17:34.11,Default,,0,0,0,,into errors later.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:34.87,0:17:37.01,Default,,0,0,0,,You can also try to infer what a
Dialogue: 0,0:17:37.01,0:17:38.95,Default,,0,0,0,,person was wishing to do, or
Dialogue: 0,0:17:38.95,0:17:40.94,Default,,0,0,0,,what they intended to do when
Dialogue: 0,0:17:40.94,0:17:42.76,Default,,0,0,0,,they made a mistake, and then do
Dialogue: 0,0:17:42.76,0:17:44.07,Default,,0,0,0,,something reasonable.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:44.95,0:17:47.18,Default,,0,0,0,,So, for example, in the new
Dialogue: 0,0:17:47.18,0:17:49.67,Default,,0,0,0,,version of Things 3, if you type
Dialogue: 0,0:17:49.67,0:17:52.59,Default,,0,0,0,,in the date June 31st, which by
Dialogue: 0,0:17:52.59,0:17:53.66,Default,,0,0,0,,the way is a date that does not
Dialogue: 0,0:17:53.66,0:17:55.35,Default,,0,0,0,,exist, but it's a common mistake
Dialogue: 0,0:17:55.41,0:17:57.23,Default,,0,0,0,,for people to make, the app
Dialogue: 0,0:17:57.35,0:17:59.54,Default,,0,0,0,,doesn't throw up an error or
Dialogue: 0,0:17:59.54,0:18:00.58,Default,,0,0,0,,show a warning.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:01.30,0:18:03.24,Default,,0,0,0,,No. Instead, it automatically
Dialogue: 0,0:18:03.24,0:18:05.32,Default,,0,0,0,,corrects the date to July 1st.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:06.15,0:18:08.23,Default,,0,0,0,,It's such a subtle thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:08.85,0:18:10.52,Default,,0,0,0,,It's kind of brilliant, and it's
Dialogue: 0,0:18:10.52,0:18:12.57,Default,,0,0,0,,a very human thing to do.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:13.95,0:18:15.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, as you can see, clear,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:15.66,0:18:17.27,Default,,0,0,0,,timely, and understandable and
Dialogue: 0,0:18:17.27,0:18:18.84,Default,,0,0,0,,informative feedback is
Dialogue: 0,0:18:18.84,0:18:19.38,Default,,0,0,0,,essential.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:19.92,0:18:21.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Feedback answers super important
Dialogue: 0,0:18:21.78,0:18:22.43,Default,,0,0,0,,questions.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:22.96,0:18:24.09,Default,,0,0,0,,What can I do?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:25.21,0:18:26.29,Default,,0,0,0,,What just happened?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:27.22,0:18:28.88,Default,,0,0,0,,What is currently happening?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:29.51,0:18:31.18,Default,,0,0,0,,And what will happen in the
Dialogue: 0,0:18:31.18,0:18:31.65,Default,,0,0,0,,future?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:32.18,0:18:35.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Many apps do not do a very good
Dialogue: 0,0:18:35.38,0:18:36.71,Default,,0,0,0,,job of providing feedback.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:38.20,0:18:40.31,Default,,0,0,0,,The reason for this, I think, is
Dialogue: 0,0:18:40.31,0:18:41.54,Default,,0,0,0,,that when you're designing, it
Dialogue: 0,0:18:41.54,0:18:42.82,Default,,0,0,0,,is so easy to start to think
Dialogue: 0,0:18:42.82,0:18:44.64,Default,,0,0,0,,about static screens, and you
Dialogue: 0,0:18:44.64,0:18:46.08,Default,,0,0,0,,can lose sight of the fact that
Dialogue: 0,0:18:46.08,0:18:47.82,Default,,0,0,0,,interactive experiences happen
Dialogue: 0,0:18:47.82,0:18:50.51,Default,,0,0,0,,over time, with lots of back and
Dialogue: 0,0:18:50.60,0:18:50.93,Default,,0,0,0,,forth.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:52.13,0:18:53.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Good feedback is like having a
Dialogue: 0,0:18:53.87,0:18:55.41,Default,,0,0,0,,conversation with the person who
Dialogue: 0,0:18:55.41,0:18:55.97,Default,,0,0,0,,designed it.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:56.82,0:18:58.87,Default,,0,0,0,,As a designer, feedback is your
Dialogue: 0,0:18:58.87,0:19:01.13,Default,,0,0,0,,way of letting -- answering
Dialogue: 0,0:19:01.13,0:19:03.06,Default,,0,0,0,,people's unspoken questions.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:03.84,0:19:05.02,Default,,0,0,0,,It is your way of letting people
Dialogue: 0,0:19:05.02,0:19:06.66,Default,,0,0,0,,know how they're doing, and
Dialogue: 0,0:19:06.66,0:19:07.90,Default,,0,0,0,,providing helpful guidance to
Dialogue: 0,0:19:07.90,0:19:08.11,Default,,0,0,0,,them.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:08.87,0:19:10.71,Default,,0,0,0,,So when designing your app,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:11.33,0:19:12.55,Default,,0,0,0,,imagine that you're having a
Dialogue: 0,0:19:12.55,0:19:14.88,Default,,0,0,0,,conversation with the person who
Dialogue: 0,0:19:14.88,0:19:15.35,Default,,0,0,0,,is using it.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:16.28,0:19:17.92,Default,,0,0,0,,What would you say if you were
Dialogue: 0,0:19:17.92,0:19:19.27,Default,,0,0,0,,in the room with them?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:20.22,0:19:21.13,Default,,0,0,0,,How would you say it?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:22.41,0:19:24.00,Default,,0,0,0,,I have a very simple, but highly
Dialogue: 0,0:19:24.00,0:19:25.15,Default,,0,0,0,,effective technique to share
Dialogue: 0,0:19:25.15,0:19:25.50,Default,,0,0,0,,with you.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:25.99,0:19:27.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Ask someone who has never used
Dialogue: 0,0:19:27.46,0:19:28.60,Default,,0,0,0,,your app before to use it.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:28.99,0:19:30.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Have them tell you what they are
Dialogue: 0,0:19:30.74,0:19:32.00,Default,,0,0,0,,thinking, what they think is
Dialogue: 0,0:19:32.00,0:19:33.70,Default,,0,0,0,,unclear, what they find to be
Dialogue: 0,0:19:33.70,0:19:34.36,Default,,0,0,0,,confusing.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:35.30,0:19:37.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Then simply explain to them how
Dialogue: 0,0:19:37.90,0:19:39.59,Default,,0,0,0,,your app actually works.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:40.10,0:19:41.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Guide them along, explain to
Dialogue: 0,0:19:41.76,0:19:43.55,Default,,0,0,0,,them what's happening, and what
Dialogue: 0,0:19:43.55,0:19:44.83,Default,,0,0,0,,they should be paying attention
Dialogue: 0,0:19:44.87,0:19:45.09,Default,,0,0,0,,to.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:46.17,0:19:47.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Then step back.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:48.24,0:19:50.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Consider how what you've said
Dialogue: 0,0:19:50.16,0:19:51.77,Default,,0,0,0,,might differ from what the app
Dialogue: 0,0:19:51.77,0:19:52.76,Default,,0,0,0,,is communicating.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:53.37,0:19:54.89,Default,,0,0,0,,In my experience, when someone
Dialogue: 0,0:19:54.89,0:19:56.58,Default,,0,0,0,,needs to explain their design to
Dialogue: 0,0:19:56.58,0:19:58.89,Default,,0,0,0,,me, it is usually so much more
Dialogue: 0,0:19:58.89,0:20:02.98,Default,,0,0,0,,clear than the design itself.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:03.05,0:20:04.23,Default,,0,0,0,,What people tell me fills in the
Dialogue: 0,0:20:04.23,0:20:06.01,Default,,0,0,0,,gaps that are left by their
Dialogue: 0,0:20:06.01,0:20:06.53,Default,,0,0,0,,design.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:07.61,0:20:09.10,Default,,0,0,0,,We tend to be much better
Dialogue: 0,0:20:09.10,0:20:10.86,Default,,0,0,0,,communicators when we're sitting
Dialogue: 0,0:20:10.86,0:20:12.91,Default,,0,0,0,,with someone in person to try to
Dialogue: 0,0:20:12.95,0:20:14.54,Default,,0,0,0,,capture that experience.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:15.56,0:20:16.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay, so that is feedback.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:17.45,0:20:18.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, the next design principle
Dialogue: 0,0:20:18.92,0:20:20.68,Default,,0,0,0,,is closely related to feedback,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:21.13,0:20:22.52,Default,,0,0,0,,and that is the principle of
Dialogue: 0,0:20:22.52,0:20:23.30,Default,,0,0,0,,visibility.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:24.25,0:20:26.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Good feedback does not matter
Dialogue: 0,0:20:26.16,0:20:27.84,Default,,0,0,0,,very much if people can't see
Dialogue: 0,0:20:27.84,0:20:27.99,Default,,0,0,0,,it.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:28.82,0:20:30.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Visibility captures something
Dialogue: 0,0:20:30.67,0:20:31.76,Default,,0,0,0,,very obvious.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:32.27,0:20:34.13,Default,,0,0,0,,The usability of a design is
Dialogue: 0,0:20:34.16,0:20:36.52,Default,,0,0,0,,greatly improved when controls
Dialogue: 0,0:20:36.52,0:20:38.45,Default,,0,0,0,,and information are clearly
Dialogue: 0,0:20:38.45,0:20:38.97,Default,,0,0,0,,visible.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:39.79,0:20:41.60,Default,,0,0,0,,See? It's kind of obvious.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:42.39,0:20:43.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Consider how important
Dialogue: 0,0:20:43.77,0:20:45.78,Default,,0,0,0,,visibility is in your car.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:46.63,0:20:48.04,Default,,0,0,0,,The instrument cluster presents
Dialogue: 0,0:20:48.04,0:20:49.49,Default,,0,0,0,,status information and warning
Dialogue: 0,0:20:49.49,0:20:51.37,Default,,0,0,0,,indicators directly in front of
Dialogue: 0,0:20:51.37,0:20:51.60,Default,,0,0,0,,you.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:52.05,0:20:53.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Instrument clusters are visually
Dialogue: 0,0:20:53.77,0:20:54.20,Default,,0,0,0,,cluttered.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:54.20,0:20:55.20,Default,,0,0,0,,There's all sorts of text, and
Dialogue: 0,0:20:55.30,0:20:56.72,Default,,0,0,0,,numbers and moving gauges and
Dialogue: 0,0:20:56.72,0:20:57.79,Default,,0,0,0,,blinking lights and status
Dialogue: 0,0:20:57.79,0:20:58.44,Default,,0,0,0,,indicators.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:59.52,0:21:00.97,Default,,0,0,0,,They're not called clusters
Dialogue: 0,0:21:01.14,0:21:01.76,Default,,0,0,0,,without reason.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:02.76,0:21:05.26,Default,,0,0,0,,But all of this is necessary for
Dialogue: 0,0:21:05.26,0:21:07.42,Default,,0,0,0,,operating a vehicle, and needs
Dialogue: 0,0:21:07.42,0:21:10.32,Default,,0,0,0,,to be plainly visible, without
Dialogue: 0,0:21:10.32,0:21:11.91,Default,,0,0,0,,you having to move your head or
Dialogue: 0,0:21:11.91,0:21:12.35,Default,,0,0,0,,your body.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:13.59,0:21:15.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Hiding some of this information
Dialogue: 0,0:21:15.18,0:21:17.08,Default,,0,0,0,,or putting it elsewhere in the
Dialogue: 0,0:21:17.08,0:21:19.28,Default,,0,0,0,,car would hurt usability.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:19.95,0:21:21.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Critical feedback would just get
Dialogue: 0,0:21:21.53,0:21:23.68,Default,,0,0,0,,ignored, and the same is true
Dialogue: 0,0:21:23.68,0:21:24.39,Default,,0,0,0,,for apps.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:25.25,0:21:27.58,Default,,0,0,0,,In the Mail app, badges provide
Dialogue: 0,0:21:27.58,0:21:29.43,Default,,0,0,0,,helpful status information about
Dialogue: 0,0:21:29.43,0:21:30.46,Default,,0,0,0,,email messages.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:31.11,0:21:33.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Removing that information might
Dialogue: 0,0:21:33.22,0:21:34.03,Default,,0,0,0,,reduce clutter.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:34.03,0:21:34.75,Default,,0,0,0,,It could look a little bit
Dialogue: 0,0:21:34.75,0:21:37.20,Default,,0,0,0,,cleaner, but it would greatly
Dialogue: 0,0:21:37.25,0:21:38.20,Default,,0,0,0,,reduce usability.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:38.92,0:21:40.14,Default,,0,0,0,,People would have to navigate
Dialogue: 0,0:21:40.83,0:21:42.67,Default,,0,0,0,,into each email message to get
Dialogue: 0,0:21:42.67,0:21:43.49,Default,,0,0,0,,that information.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:44.24,0:21:45.51,Default,,0,0,0,,It would be very inefficient,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:45.77,0:21:47.13,Default,,0,0,0,,and it would be very tedious.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:47.85,0:21:49.33,Default,,0,0,0,,So it is important to surface
Dialogue: 0,0:21:49.42,0:21:51.38,Default,,0,0,0,,key status information at higher
Dialogue: 0,0:21:51.38,0:21:53.22,Default,,0,0,0,,levels whenever possible.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:54.38,0:21:56.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Or, consider the navigation in
Dialogue: 0,0:21:56.18,0:21:56.73,Default,,0,0,0,,the Clock app.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:57.58,0:21:59.57,Default,,0,0,0,,What if that was hidden into a
Dialogue: 0,0:21:59.57,0:22:00.37,Default,,0,0,0,,hamburger menu.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:01.25,0:22:02.73,Default,,0,0,0,,People would have a much harder
Dialogue: 0,0:22:02.80,0:22:05.00,Default,,0,0,0,,time seeing what other functions
Dialogue: 0,0:22:05.04,0:22:06.80,Default,,0,0,0,,the Clock app offers to them
Dialogue: 0,0:22:07.17,0:22:08.49,Default,,0,0,0,,beyond what is currently
Dialogue: 0,0:22:08.49,0:22:08.97,Default,,0,0,0,,visible.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:10.35,0:22:11.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Obviously there is a tradeoff
Dialogue: 0,0:22:11.72,0:22:11.98,Default,,0,0,0,,here.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:12.40,0:22:14.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Densely packed interfaces can be
Dialogue: 0,0:22:14.38,0:22:15.93,Default,,0,0,0,,overwhelming and they can slow
Dialogue: 0,0:22:15.93,0:22:18.02,Default,,0,0,0,,decision-making, especially for
Dialogue: 0,0:22:18.02,0:22:19.29,Default,,0,0,0,,people who are new to your app.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:20.24,0:22:22.22,Default,,0,0,0,,So visibility has to be weighed
Dialogue: 0,0:22:22.22,0:22:23.64,Default,,0,0,0,,against other considerations.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:25.04,0:22:27.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, with so many of us in the
Dialogue: 0,0:22:27.17,0:22:29.00,Default,,0,0,0,,car, I'm starting to feel a
Dialogue: 0,0:22:29.00,0:22:31.09,Default,,0,0,0,,little bit cramped, and I cannot
Dialogue: 0,0:22:31.09,0:22:32.69,Default,,0,0,0,,wait to get to the hotel, but
Dialogue: 0,0:22:32.69,0:22:34.74,Default,,0,0,0,,there is one more insanely
Dialogue: 0,0:22:34.74,0:22:36.74,Default,,0,0,0,,important design principle to
Dialogue: 0,0:22:36.74,0:22:38.75,Default,,0,0,0,,point out while we're here, and
Dialogue: 0,0:22:38.75,0:22:40.50,Default,,0,0,0,,that is about consistency.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:41.06,0:22:43.83,Default,,0,0,0,,The principle of consistency is
Dialogue: 0,0:22:43.83,0:22:45.59,Default,,0,0,0,,about representing similar
Dialogue: 0,0:22:45.59,0:22:48.75,Default,,0,0,0,,design features in similar ways.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:49.44,0:22:51.52,Default,,0,0,0,,If you've driven a car before,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:51.91,0:22:53.43,Default,,0,0,0,,there are symbols and terms that
Dialogue: 0,0:22:53.43,0:22:54.63,Default,,0,0,0,,you are no doubt familiar with.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:55.14,0:22:56.48,Default,,0,0,0,,You will recognize the symbols
Dialogue: 0,0:22:56.48,0:22:58.40,Default,,0,0,0,,for door lock, for window, for
Dialogue: 0,0:22:58.69,0:23:01.30,Default,,0,0,0,,gas, headlights, battery, oil,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:01.83,0:23:02.39,Default,,0,0,0,,and so forth.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:03.11,0:23:04.60,Default,,0,0,0,,You will be familiar with the
Dialogue: 0,0:23:04.60,0:23:06.91,Default,,0,0,0,,definitions of words like Park,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:06.98,0:23:08.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Drive, and Reverse, as they
Dialogue: 0,0:23:08.78,0:23:10.36,Default,,0,0,0,,apply to the operation of a
Dialogue: 0,0:23:10.36,0:23:10.87,Default,,0,0,0,,vehicle.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:12.07,0:23:13.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Consistency also applies to the
Dialogue: 0,0:23:13.98,0:23:15.89,Default,,0,0,0,,location and the configuration
Dialogue: 0,0:23:15.89,0:23:16.72,Default,,0,0,0,,of controls.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:17.32,0:23:19.09,Default,,0,0,0,,We all expect the brake to be on
Dialogue: 0,0:23:19.09,0:23:21.31,Default,,0,0,0,,the left, and the accelerator to
Dialogue: 0,0:23:21.31,0:23:22.21,Default,,0,0,0,,be on the right.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:23.66,0:23:25.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Consistency greatly improves the
Dialogue: 0,0:23:25.40,0:23:27.72,Default,,0,0,0,,usability of a vehicle, or maybe
Dialogue: 0,0:23:27.72,0:23:29.86,Default,,0,0,0,,it is more clear to just flip
Dialogue: 0,0:23:29.86,0:23:30.85,Default,,0,0,0,,this around and say that
Dialogue: 0,0:23:30.85,0:23:32.96,Default,,0,0,0,,inconsistency undermines
Dialogue: 0,0:23:33.36,0:23:34.02,Default,,0,0,0,,usability.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:34.63,0:23:38.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Whoops. All cars share a common
Dialogue: 0,0:23:38.24,0:23:40.27,Default,,0,0,0,,design vocabulary for these
Dialogue: 0,0:23:40.34,0:23:41.43,Default,,0,0,0,,symbols and terms.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:42.15,0:23:44.00,Default,,0,0,0,,All cars position controls in a
Dialogue: 0,0:23:44.04,0:23:45.44,Default,,0,0,0,,relatively consistent way, and
Dialogue: 0,0:23:45.90,0:23:47.55,Default,,0,0,0,,because of this consistency, we
Dialogue: 0,0:23:47.55,0:23:48.85,Default,,0,0,0,,don't have to re-learn how to
Dialogue: 0,0:23:48.85,0:23:50.69,Default,,0,0,0,,drive a car every time we get
Dialogue: 0,0:23:50.69,0:23:52.12,Default,,0,0,0,,behind the wheel of a new one.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:52.85,0:23:54.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, maybe this is obvious, but
Dialogue: 0,0:23:54.79,0:23:57.09,Default,,0,0,0,,consistency is actually hard to
Dialogue: 0,0:23:57.09,0:23:57.49,Default,,0,0,0,,achieve.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:58.22,0:23:59.87,Default,,0,0,0,,You have to make a conscious
Dialogue: 0,0:23:59.98,0:24:02.96,Default,,0,0,0,,effort to be consistent, and you
Dialogue: 0,0:24:02.96,0:24:04.86,Default,,0,0,0,,have to be consistent with the
Dialogue: 0,0:24:04.86,0:24:05.55,Default,,0,0,0,,right things.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:05.55,0:24:08.32,Default,,0,0,0,,You have to fully consider what
Dialogue: 0,0:24:08.32,0:24:09.79,Default,,0,0,0,,expectations people have when
Dialogue: 0,0:24:09.79,0:24:10.64,Default,,0,0,0,,they come to your app.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:11.20,0:24:13.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Those expectations are mostly
Dialogue: 0,0:24:13.05,0:24:15.18,Default,,0,0,0,,informed by their experiences
Dialogue: 0,0:24:15.18,0:24:16.56,Default,,0,0,0,,with the other apps that they
Dialogue: 0,0:24:16.56,0:24:17.18,Default,,0,0,0,,use.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:17.99,0:24:19.54,Default,,0,0,0,,The other apps that they use,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:19.54,0:24:20.71,Default,,0,0,0,,how do you figure that out?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:20.71,0:24:22.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Of course, it is impossible for
Dialogue: 0,0:24:22.18,0:24:22.76,Default,,0,0,0,,you to know.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:23.32,0:24:25.70,Default,,0,0,0,,But you can make some informed
Dialogue: 0,0:24:25.70,0:24:26.28,Default,,0,0,0,,guesses.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:26.90,0:24:28.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Perhaps they've used other apps
Dialogue: 0,0:24:28.47,0:24:29.68,Default,,0,0,0,,that are similar to the things
Dialogue: 0,0:24:29.68,0:24:30.69,Default,,0,0,0,,that your app does.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:31.33,0:24:31.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Maybe not.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:32.66,0:24:34.80,Default,,0,0,0,,But it's very likely that they
Dialogue: 0,0:24:34.80,0:24:36.10,Default,,0,0,0,,have used other apps on the
Dialogue: 0,0:24:36.10,0:24:36.77,Default,,0,0,0,,platform.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:37.11,0:24:38.71,Default,,0,0,0,,So you should pay attention to
Dialogue: 0,0:24:38.74,0:24:40.16,Default,,0,0,0,,platform conventions.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:40.78,0:24:42.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Things like iconography and
Dialogue: 0,0:24:43.05,0:24:45.11,Default,,0,0,0,,terminology, navigation schemes,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:45.62,0:24:47.69,Default,,0,0,0,,and even common work flows for
Dialogue: 0,0:24:47.69,0:24:48.65,Default,,0,0,0,,typical tasks.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:49.84,0:24:51.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, let me give you just one
Dialogue: 0,0:24:51.93,0:24:53.60,Default,,0,0,0,,example to make this, I think, a
Dialogue: 0,0:24:53.60,0:24:54.88,Default,,0,0,0,,lot more concrete.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:55.72,0:24:58.00,Default,,0,0,0,,On iOS, the glyph that we use to
Dialogue: 0,0:24:58.00,0:24:59.68,Default,,0,0,0,,represent the concept of an
Dialogue: 0,0:24:59.85,0:25:01.80,Default,,0,0,0,,action is an arrow that points
Dialogue: 0,0:25:01.80,0:25:03.30,Default,,0,0,0,,up and away from a box.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:04.21,0:25:05.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Because the most common action
Dialogue: 0,0:25:05.92,0:25:08.02,Default,,0,0,0,,associated with this glyph is
Dialogue: 0,0:25:08.02,0:25:10.01,Default,,0,0,0,,share, we affectionately call
Dialogue: 0,0:25:10.01,0:25:11.46,Default,,0,0,0,,this a "sharrow."
Dialogue: 0,0:25:11.59,0:25:13.97,Default,,0,0,0,,I love that name.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:14.73,0:25:16.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, some apps use a different
Dialogue: 0,0:25:16.63,0:25:18.57,Default,,0,0,0,,icon to represent a similar
Dialogue: 0,0:25:18.57,0:25:19.15,Default,,0,0,0,,concept.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:19.89,0:25:21.85,Default,,0,0,0,,This icon is commonplace.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:21.85,0:25:23.74,Default,,0,0,0,,It is used on websites and other
Dialogue: 0,0:25:23.74,0:25:24.43,Default,,0,0,0,,platforms.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:24.98,0:25:26.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, this is a great glyph.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:26.96,0:25:28.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Do not get me wrong.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:28.30,0:25:29.49,Default,,0,0,0,,There is nothing wrong with this
Dialogue: 0,0:25:29.49,0:25:30.38,Default,,0,0,0,,glyph at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:30.75,0:25:32.92,Default,,0,0,0,,But it's not the symbol that iOS
Dialogue: 0,0:25:32.92,0:25:34.56,Default,,0,0,0,,users are most familiar with.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:35.35,0:25:37.54,Default,,0,0,0,,This glyph shows up in iOS apps
Dialogue: 0,0:25:37.86,0:25:39.60,Default,,0,0,0,,because of the desire to be
Dialogue: 0,0:25:39.63,0:25:41.84,Default,,0,0,0,,consistent, to consistently
Dialogue: 0,0:25:41.84,0:25:43.44,Default,,0,0,0,,represent this concept in a
Dialogue: 0,0:25:43.44,0:25:46.54,Default,,0,0,0,,consistent way across platforms
Dialogue: 0,0:25:46.54,0:25:47.71,Default,,0,0,0,,or with your website.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:48.68,0:25:51.09,Default,,0,0,0,,This is a perfectly rational and
Dialogue: 0,0:25:51.09,0:25:53.28,Default,,0,0,0,,reasonable thing to do, but it
Dialogue: 0,0:25:53.28,0:25:54.57,Default,,0,0,0,,is not the right call.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:55.27,0:25:56.57,Default,,0,0,0,,From the perspective of the
Dialogue: 0,0:25:56.57,0:25:57.83,Default,,0,0,0,,person who you are designing
Dialogue: 0,0:25:57.88,0:25:59.96,Default,,0,0,0,,for, it is best to be consistent
Dialogue: 0,0:26:00.21,0:26:01.19,Default,,0,0,0,,with the symbol that they are
Dialogue: 0,0:26:01.19,0:26:02.24,Default,,0,0,0,,most familiar with.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:03.52,0:26:05.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Being consistent will go a long
Dialogue: 0,0:26:05.41,0:26:07.48,Default,,0,0,0,,way towards making your app more
Dialogue: 0,0:26:07.48,0:26:09.21,Default,,0,0,0,,approachable and usable.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:09.21,0:26:13.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, look, there is always the
Dialogue: 0,0:26:13.07,0:26:15.67,Default,,0,0,0,,impulse to, you know, do things
Dialogue: 0,0:26:15.67,0:26:16.55,Default,,0,0,0,,a little bit different.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:17.29,0:26:19.49,Default,,0,0,0,,And to be clear, this is a
Dialogue: 0,0:26:19.49,0:26:20.61,Default,,0,0,0,,really good thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:20.61,0:26:24.12,Default,,0,0,0,,You should absolutely be trying
Dialogue: 0,0:26:24.12,0:26:25.57,Default,,0,0,0,,out new ideas.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:25.66,0:26:27.22,Default,,0,0,0,,That's how innovation happens.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:28.13,0:26:30.14,Default,,0,0,0,,But inconsistencies about simple
Dialogue: 0,0:26:30.14,0:26:32.28,Default,,0,0,0,,things, like icons and labels,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:32.28,0:26:33.70,Default,,0,0,0,,can really trip people up.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:34.43,0:26:36.13,Default,,0,0,0,,So it's always best to be
Dialogue: 0,0:26:36.13,0:26:37.56,Default,,0,0,0,,consistent unless you have a
Dialogue: 0,0:26:37.56,0:26:40.05,Default,,0,0,0,,very strong justification to do
Dialogue: 0,0:26:40.05,0:26:40.68,Default,,0,0,0,,otherwise.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:41.90,0:26:43.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, I'm sure you're all
Dialogue: 0,0:26:43.03,0:26:44.18,Default,,0,0,0,,consistently ready to get out of
Dialogue: 0,0:26:44.18,0:26:45.41,Default,,0,0,0,,this car and get to the hotel,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:45.60,0:26:46.74,Default,,0,0,0,,but there is one last point
Dialogue: 0,0:26:46.74,0:26:47.94,Default,,0,0,0,,about consistency that I'd like
Dialogue: 0,0:26:48.01,0:26:49.42,Default,,0,0,0,,to make, and it is about
Dialogue: 0,0:26:49.42,0:26:50.49,Default,,0,0,0,,internal consistency.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:51.57,0:26:53.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Internal consistency is about
Dialogue: 0,0:26:53.44,0:26:55.39,Default,,0,0,0,,designing controls to share a
Dialogue: 0,0:26:55.39,0:26:57.36,Default,,0,0,0,,similar look and feel, that
Dialogue: 0,0:26:57.36,0:26:58.17,Default,,0,0,0,,match each other.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:58.82,0:27:00.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Your app's glyphs should have a
Dialogue: 0,0:27:00.89,0:27:02.57,Default,,0,0,0,,consistent visual style.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:03.25,0:27:04.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Text in your app should have a
Dialogue: 0,0:27:04.78,0:27:06.61,Default,,0,0,0,,limited number of font faces and
Dialogue: 0,0:27:06.61,0:27:09.16,Default,,0,0,0,,sizes and colors and so forth.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:10.21,0:27:12.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Internal consistency helps to
Dialogue: 0,0:27:12.48,0:27:15.29,Default,,0,0,0,,make an app feel cohesive or
Dialogue: 0,0:27:15.29,0:27:15.75,Default,,0,0,0,,whole.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:16.67,0:27:18.42,Default,,0,0,0,,When everything matches, when
Dialogue: 0,0:27:18.42,0:27:20.30,Default,,0,0,0,,everything fits, people are
Dialogue: 0,0:27:20.30,0:27:21.73,Default,,0,0,0,,given a deeper sense of a
Dialogue: 0,0:27:21.73,0:27:23.10,Default,,0,0,0,,product's integrity.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:23.81,0:27:25.89,Default,,0,0,0,,We intuitively believe that
Dialogue: 0,0:27:25.93,0:27:28.06,Default,,0,0,0,,design choices were deliberate
Dialogue: 0,0:27:28.50,0:27:29.86,Default,,0,0,0,,and thoroughly considered.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:31.08,0:27:32.34,Default,,0,0,0,,And with very good reason.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:32.72,0:27:34.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Being consistent takes
Dialogue: 0,0:27:34.48,0:27:36.31,Default,,0,0,0,,self-control and restraint.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:37.45,0:27:39.05,Default,,0,0,0,,All right, now because our car
Dialogue: 0,0:27:39.05,0:27:40.61,Default,,0,0,0,,was so darn consistent, we
Dialogue: 0,0:27:40.61,0:27:42.40,Default,,0,0,0,,finally managed to arrive safely
Dialogue: 0,0:27:42.40,0:27:43.21,Default,,0,0,0,,at the hotel.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:44.27,0:27:46.08,Default,,0,0,0,,That car ride was really stuffy.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:46.27,0:27:47.55,Default,,0,0,0,,So you decide to head up to your
Dialogue: 0,0:27:47.55,0:27:49.37,Default,,0,0,0,,room and freshen up a little
Dialogue: 0,0:27:49.65,0:27:49.74,Default,,0,0,0,,bit.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:50.06,0:27:51.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Perhaps you go throw on that
Dialogue: 0,0:27:51.52,0:27:53.43,Default,,0,0,0,,fresh new Aloha shirt you picked
Dialogue: 0,0:27:53.43,0:27:54.20,Default,,0,0,0,,up at the airport.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:55.03,0:27:56.30,Default,,0,0,0,,So, when you get to your room,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:56.80,0:27:58.78,Default,,0,0,0,,you head to the bathroom, and
Dialogue: 0,0:27:58.78,0:28:00.27,Default,,0,0,0,,you turn the handles on the
Dialogue: 0,0:28:00.27,0:28:02.26,Default,,0,0,0,,faucet and let the water run a
Dialogue: 0,0:28:02.26,0:28:03.73,Default,,0,0,0,,little bit.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:03.73,0:28:05.13,Default,,0,0,0,,And after a couple of seconds
Dialogue: 0,0:28:05.50,0:28:06.55,Default,,0,0,0,,you put your finger under the
Dialogue: 0,0:28:06.55,0:28:07.79,Default,,0,0,0,,water to check the temperature.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:08.48,0:28:10.35,Default,,0,0,0,,It's still a little bit cool, so
Dialogue: 0,0:28:10.35,0:28:11.52,Default,,0,0,0,,you increase the hot water a
Dialogue: 0,0:28:11.52,0:28:12.04,Default,,0,0,0,,little bit.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:12.56,0:28:13.68,Default,,0,0,0,,You wait another couple of
Dialogue: 0,0:28:13.68,0:28:15.15,Default,,0,0,0,,seconds, and the water warms up,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:15.49,0:28:17.14,Default,,0,0,0,,and you commence face washing.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:18.09,0:28:20.54,Default,,0,0,0,,You feel refreshed and
Dialogue: 0,0:28:20.54,0:28:21.40,Default,,0,0,0,,reinvigorated.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:23.05,0:28:24.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Compared to driving a car, a
Dialogue: 0,0:28:25.02,0:28:26.91,Default,,0,0,0,,faucet is really basic.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:27.72,0:28:29.37,Default,,0,0,0,,But at some point, you had to
Dialogue: 0,0:28:29.37,0:28:30.85,Default,,0,0,0,,learn how to use a faucet.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:31.61,0:28:32.89,Default,,0,0,0,,You learned by adjusting the
Dialogue: 0,0:28:32.89,0:28:34.38,Default,,0,0,0,,controls of various faucets and
Dialogue: 0,0:28:34.38,0:28:35.89,Default,,0,0,0,,observing the results.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:36.87,0:28:38.23,Default,,0,0,0,,For example, how do you know
Dialogue: 0,0:28:38.23,0:28:39.50,Default,,0,0,0,,which handle controlled the hot
Dialogue: 0,0:28:39.50,0:28:39.88,Default,,0,0,0,,water?
Dialogue: 0,0:28:40.58,0:28:42.78,Default,,0,0,0,,You knew because for the most
Dialogue: 0,0:28:42.78,0:28:44.58,Default,,0,0,0,,part hot water is controlled by
Dialogue: 0,0:28:44.58,0:28:45.78,Default,,0,0,0,,the handle on the left.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:47.20,0:28:48.53,Default,,0,0,0,,And why would you keep testing
Dialogue: 0,0:28:48.53,0:28:49.73,Default,,0,0,0,,water temperature for a few
Dialogue: 0,0:28:49.73,0:28:50.19,Default,,0,0,0,,seconds?
Dialogue: 0,0:28:50.69,0:28:52.08,Default,,0,0,0,,You did this, because you expect
Dialogue: 0,0:28:52.08,0:28:53.29,Default,,0,0,0,,there to be a delay between when
Dialogue: 0,0:28:53.29,0:28:54.84,Default,,0,0,0,,you adjust the temperature and
Dialogue: 0,0:28:54.84,0:28:56.14,Default,,0,0,0,,when the water actually gets
Dialogue: 0,0:28:56.14,0:28:56.58,Default,,0,0,0,,warmer.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:56.58,0:28:59.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Looking at the water, it is
Dialogue: 0,0:28:59.58,0:29:01.05,Default,,0,0,0,,really hard to tell if the water
Dialogue: 0,0:29:01.05,0:29:03.55,Default,,0,0,0,,is cold or hot, and we have all
Dialogue: 0,0:29:03.55,0:29:05.04,Default,,0,0,0,,experienced burning our hand
Dialogue: 0,0:29:05.04,0:29:05.92,Default,,0,0,0,,under a faucet.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:06.84,0:29:08.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, you don't think about these
Dialogue: 0,0:29:08.35,0:29:09.97,Default,,0,0,0,,things every time you use a
Dialogue: 0,0:29:10.04,0:29:10.52,Default,,0,0,0,,faucet.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:10.92,0:29:12.83,Default,,0,0,0,,You just intuitively expect
Dialogue: 0,0:29:12.83,0:29:13.00,Default,,0,0,0,,them.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:14.15,0:29:16.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Within each of your brains,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:16.64,0:29:18.35,Default,,0,0,0,,there is this tiny, little
Dialogue: 0,0:29:18.82,0:29:22.38,Default,,0,0,0,,adorable model of a faucet, and
Dialogue: 0,0:29:22.38,0:29:24.58,Default,,0,0,0,,that model represents the faucet
Dialogue: 0,0:29:24.96,0:29:27.05,Default,,0,0,0,,as a system of parts and
Dialogue: 0,0:29:27.11,0:29:28.92,Default,,0,0,0,,functions and behaviors.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:30.62,0:29:32.37,Default,,0,0,0,,There is a spout for producing
Dialogue: 0,0:29:32.37,0:29:34.02,Default,,0,0,0,,water, there's handles for
Dialogue: 0,0:29:34.02,0:29:35.15,Default,,0,0,0,,controlling temperature and
Dialogue: 0,0:29:35.15,0:29:35.49,Default,,0,0,0,,flow.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:36.43,0:29:37.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Those parts are arranged in
Dialogue: 0,0:29:37.99,0:29:41.45,Default,,0,0,0,,specific configuration, and your
Dialogue: 0,0:29:41.45,0:29:43.12,Default,,0,0,0,,model has certain behaviors,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:43.12,0:29:44.81,Default,,0,0,0,,like the latency between when
Dialogue: 0,0:29:44.81,0:29:46.33,Default,,0,0,0,,you adjust the hot water, and
Dialogue: 0,0:29:46.33,0:29:47.12,Default,,0,0,0,,when the temperature of the
Dialogue: 0,0:29:47.12,0:29:48.86,Default,,0,0,0,,water actually increases.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:49.87,0:29:52.21,Default,,0,0,0,,This model is referred to as
Dialogue: 0,0:29:52.21,0:29:53.74,Default,,0,0,0,,your mental model.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:54.72,0:29:56.52,Default,,0,0,0,,You have a mental model of every
Dialogue: 0,0:29:56.58,0:29:57.67,Default,,0,0,0,,system that you've ever
Dialogue: 0,0:29:57.67,0:29:58.40,Default,,0,0,0,,interacted with.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:59.15,0:30:00.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Those mental models are
Dialogue: 0,0:30:00.68,0:30:02.03,Default,,0,0,0,,over-simplifications.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:02.45,0:30:03.85,Default,,0,0,0,,They don't fully capture the
Dialogue: 0,0:30:03.85,0:30:05.43,Default,,0,0,0,,inner workings of these systems.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:05.43,0:30:07.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Though, the more experience you
Dialogue: 0,0:30:07.12,0:30:08.96,Default,,0,0,0,,have with a system, the more
Dialogue: 0,0:30:08.96,0:30:12.59,Default,,0,0,0,,sophisticated your model
Dialogue: 0,0:30:12.59,0:30:12.98,Default,,0,0,0,,becomes.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:13.05,0:30:13.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Mental models are developed
Dialogue: 0,0:30:13.89,0:30:15.28,Default,,0,0,0,,through personal experience, and
Dialogue: 0,0:30:15.28,0:30:16.69,Default,,0,0,0,,they're based on an incomplete
Dialogue: 0,0:30:16.79,0:30:18.88,Default,,0,0,0,,set of facts, so everyone's
Dialogue: 0,0:30:18.88,0:30:20.43,Default,,0,0,0,,mental model is unique.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:21.39,0:30:22.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, real quick, there is
Dialogue: 0,0:30:22.55,0:30:24.37,Default,,0,0,0,,actually two parts of a mental
Dialogue: 0,0:30:24.37,0:30:25.50,Default,,0,0,0,,model that are worth
Dialogue: 0,0:30:25.50,0:30:26.72,Default,,0,0,0,,understanding separately.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:27.22,0:30:29.15,Default,,0,0,0,,A system model is the model
Dialogue: 0,0:30:29.81,0:30:31.62,Default,,0,0,0,,about how a system works.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:32.44,0:30:33.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Our system model might involve
Dialogue: 0,0:30:33.89,0:30:35.30,Default,,0,0,0,,thinking about two independent
Dialogue: 0,0:30:35.30,0:30:37.15,Default,,0,0,0,,sources of water, one hot, and
Dialogue: 0,0:30:37.15,0:30:37.81,Default,,0,0,0,,one cold.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:38.81,0:30:40.20,Default,,0,0,0,,And the system allows those
Dialogue: 0,0:30:40.20,0:30:41.96,Default,,0,0,0,,inputs to be mixed, to create a
Dialogue: 0,0:30:42.04,0:30:43.10,Default,,0,0,0,,range of temperatures.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:43.95,0:30:45.23,Default,,0,0,0,,The system is not immediately
Dialogue: 0,0:30:45.23,0:30:46.00,Default,,0,0,0,,responsive.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:46.20,0:30:47.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Changes to temperature could
Dialogue: 0,0:30:47.18,0:30:48.23,Default,,0,0,0,,take a little bit of time,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:49.13,0:30:50.70,Default,,0,0,0,,especially when we first turn on
Dialogue: 0,0:30:50.70,0:30:51.53,Default,,0,0,0,,the faucet, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:30:51.82,0:30:53.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Our system model includes this
Dialogue: 0,0:30:53.33,0:30:55.47,Default,,0,0,0,,understanding of variable
Dialogue: 0,0:30:55.52,0:30:56.73,Default,,0,0,0,,latency and temperature.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:57.99,0:31:00.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay. The other term is
Dialogue: 0,0:31:00.09,0:31:01.17,Default,,0,0,0,,interaction model.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:01.54,0:31:03.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, does anyone care to guess
Dialogue: 0,0:31:03.82,0:31:05.03,Default,,0,0,0,,what that model is?
Dialogue: 0,0:31:05.42,0:31:06.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Just go ahead and shout it out.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:07.76,0:31:08.46,Default,,0,0,0,,No, I'm just kidding.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:08.56,0:31:10.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay, you guys didn't fall for
Dialogue: 0,0:31:10.41,0:31:10.50,Default,,0,0,0,,that.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:10.50,0:31:11.18,Default,,0,0,0,,You're a smart crowd.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:11.67,0:31:13.63,Default,,0,0,0,,If you guessed that it's a model
Dialogue: 0,0:31:13.63,0:31:15.09,Default,,0,0,0,,about how we interact with the
Dialogue: 0,0:31:15.09,0:31:17.03,Default,,0,0,0,,system, then you are correct.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:18.11,0:31:20.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Our interaction model is that we
Dialogue: 0,0:31:20.15,0:31:21.78,Default,,0,0,0,,adjust the temperature and water
Dialogue: 0,0:31:21.78,0:31:23.41,Default,,0,0,0,,flow with the handles that are
Dialogue: 0,0:31:23.41,0:31:23.94,Default,,0,0,0,,provided.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:25.07,0:31:26.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay, so now that we know a
Dialogue: 0,0:31:26.71,0:31:28.42,Default,,0,0,0,,couple of fancy terms, you might
Dialogue: 0,0:31:28.42,0:31:30.04,Default,,0,0,0,,be wondering how all of this is
Dialogue: 0,0:31:30.04,0:31:30.78,Default,,0,0,0,,relevant to you?
Dialogue: 0,0:31:31.52,0:31:34.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, when a system such as a
Dialogue: 0,0:31:34.32,0:31:36.53,Default,,0,0,0,,faucet matches our mental model,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:36.76,0:31:38.04,Default,,0,0,0,,then our expectations of that
Dialogue: 0,0:31:38.04,0:31:38.72,Default,,0,0,0,,system are met.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:39.34,0:31:40.79,Default,,0,0,0,,When this happens, and we're not
Dialogue: 0,0:31:40.79,0:31:42.35,Default,,0,0,0,,really conscious of our own
Dialogue: 0,0:31:42.35,0:31:44.68,Default,,0,0,0,,expectations, we perceive the
Dialogue: 0,0:31:44.74,0:31:46.31,Default,,0,0,0,,system to be intuitive.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:47.87,0:31:49.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Conversely, when a system
Dialogue: 0,0:31:49.77,0:31:51.28,Default,,0,0,0,,doesn't match our mental model,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:51.54,0:31:53.38,Default,,0,0,0,,it breaks our expectations, and
Dialogue: 0,0:31:53.38,0:31:54.73,Default,,0,0,0,,we perceive it to be
Dialogue: 0,0:31:54.73,0:31:55.70,Default,,0,0,0,,unintuitive.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:57.24,0:31:58.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, let's just sit with this
Dialogue: 0,0:31:58.63,0:31:59.73,Default,,0,0,0,,concept for a second.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:00.16,0:32:01.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Because it's a really, really
Dialogue: 0,0:32:01.86,0:32:03.47,Default,,0,0,0,,important one in design.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:03.72,0:32:06.64,Default,,0,0,0,,And to do that, I would like to
Dialogue: 0,0:32:06.64,0:32:08.30,Default,,0,0,0,,share with you a little story
Dialogue: 0,0:32:08.99,0:32:11.42,Default,,0,0,0,,about a faucet designer named
Dialogue: 0,0:32:11.59,0:32:12.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Mortimer.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:13.40,0:32:15.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, like all of you, Mortimer
Dialogue: 0,0:32:15.91,0:32:17.81,Default,,0,0,0,,has a mental model of faucets.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:18.33,0:32:20.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Though obviously Morty's mental
Dialogue: 0,0:32:20.10,0:32:22.25,Default,,0,0,0,,model is way more sophisticated,
Dialogue: 0,0:32:22.66,0:32:24.54,Default,,0,0,0,,and way more bad ass than yours.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:25.09,0:32:26.81,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm just being real with you, he
Dialogue: 0,0:32:26.81,0:32:27.88,Default,,0,0,0,,is a faucet designer for a
Dialogue: 0,0:32:27.88,0:32:28.25,Default,,0,0,0,,living.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:29.18,0:32:30.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, consider that job that he
Dialogue: 0,0:32:30.92,0:32:31.32,Default,,0,0,0,,has.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:32.04,0:32:33.86,Default,,0,0,0,,His job is all about making
Dialogue: 0,0:32:33.86,0:32:35.77,Default,,0,0,0,,amazing, best in class,
Dialogue: 0,0:32:36.19,0:32:38.54,Default,,0,0,0,,delightful faucet experiences.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:39.96,0:32:41.15,Default,,0,0,0,,And one day, like a bolt of
Dialogue: 0,0:32:41.15,0:32:43.16,Default,,0,0,0,,lightning, he's struck with this
Dialogue: 0,0:32:44.02,0:32:45.09,Default,,0,0,0,,amazing idea.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:45.28,0:32:47.35,Default,,0,0,0,,We have been doing this faucet
Dialogue: 0,0:32:47.40,0:32:48.58,Default,,0,0,0,,thing all wrong.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:49.22,0:32:51.40,Default,,0,0,0,,He has a new concept about how
Dialogue: 0,0:32:51.51,0:32:52.62,Default,,0,0,0,,to make things better.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:53.53,0:32:55.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Instead of using one handle for
Dialogue: 0,0:32:55.65,0:32:57.47,Default,,0,0,0,,hot water flow, and another
Dialogue: 0,0:32:57.47,0:32:59.77,Default,,0,0,0,,handle for cold water flow, we
Dialogue: 0,0:32:59.77,0:33:01.29,Default,,0,0,0,,should just have one lever to
Dialogue: 0,0:33:01.29,0:33:02.94,Default,,0,0,0,,control temperature, and the
Dialogue: 0,0:33:02.94,0:33:04.53,Default,,0,0,0,,other should control flow.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:05.10,0:33:06.07,Default,,0,0,0,,This way people won't
Dialogue: 0,0:33:06.07,0:33:07.16,Default,,0,0,0,,accidentally increase or
Dialogue: 0,0:33:07.16,0:33:08.17,Default,,0,0,0,,decrease temperature when they
Dialogue: 0,0:33:08.17,0:33:09.59,Default,,0,0,0,,are adjusting flow and vice
Dialogue: 0,0:33:09.59,0:33:09.96,Default,,0,0,0,,versa.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:11.46,0:33:13.10,Default,,0,0,0,,It is brilliant.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:14.04,0:33:15.93,Default,,0,0,0,,This is why they pay Mortimer
Dialogue: 0,0:33:16.03,0:33:16.72,Default,,0,0,0,,the big bucks.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:17.51,0:33:19.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, at this point, Morty has
Dialogue: 0,0:33:19.42,0:33:21.84,Default,,0,0,0,,this new and super awesome
Dialogue: 0,0:33:21.84,0:33:23.52,Default,,0,0,0,,mental model about faucets in
Dialogue: 0,0:33:23.52,0:33:24.12,Default,,0,0,0,,his mind.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:24.80,0:33:26.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Unfortunately, there is just one
Dialogue: 0,0:33:26.90,0:33:30.07,Default,,0,0,0,,tiny little problem.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:30.17,0:33:31.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Morty's mental model doesn't
Dialogue: 0,0:33:31.85,0:33:33.24,Default,,0,0,0,,match the mental model that
Dialogue: 0,0:33:33.24,0:33:34.94,Default,,0,0,0,,people have about faucets.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:35.69,0:33:37.09,Default,,0,0,0,,When people use the Morty
Dialogue: 0,0:33:37.09,0:33:38.65,Default,,0,0,0,,faucet, it doesn't match their
Dialogue: 0,0:33:38.65,0:33:41.12,Default,,0,0,0,,expectations at all and they say
Dialogue: 0,0:33:41.12,0:33:42.32,Default,,0,0,0,,it is unintuitive.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:43.68,0:33:45.73,Default,,0,0,0,,What is worse, the Morty faucet
Dialogue: 0,0:33:45.98,0:33:47.60,Default,,0,0,0,,looks nearly identical to a
Dialogue: 0,0:33:47.60,0:33:49.53,Default,,0,0,0,,regular faucet, but it behaved
Dialogue: 0,0:33:49.61,0:33:50.61,Default,,0,0,0,,totally different.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:51.64,0:33:52.84,Default,,0,0,0,,When people turned on the hot
Dialogue: 0,0:33:52.84,0:33:54.77,Default,,0,0,0,,water, no water came out.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:56.01,0:33:57.76,Default,,0,0,0,,This mismatch between expected
Dialogue: 0,0:33:57.76,0:34:00.08,Default,,0,0,0,,behavior and experienced reality
Dialogue: 0,0:34:00.08,0:34:02.10,Default,,0,0,0,,created a major usability
Dialogue: 0,0:34:02.10,0:34:02.61,Default,,0,0,0,,problem.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:03.65,0:34:05.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Perhaps alterations to the
Dialogue: 0,0:34:05.15,0:34:06.56,Default,,0,0,0,,faucet's form could suggest that
Dialogue: 0,0:34:06.56,0:34:07.88,Default,,0,0,0,,it had a different interaction
Dialogue: 0,0:34:07.88,0:34:08.24,Default,,0,0,0,,model.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:09.25,0:34:10.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Maybe adding labels would help,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:10.77,0:34:13.62,Default,,0,0,0,,but these are just remedies to a
Dialogue: 0,0:34:13.68,0:34:14.42,Default,,0,0,0,,deeper issue.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:15.14,0:34:16.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Labels and subtle variations of
Dialogue: 0,0:34:16.80,0:34:18.47,Default,,0,0,0,,form are design cues that can
Dialogue: 0,0:34:18.47,0:34:20.23,Default,,0,0,0,,easily be overlooked, especially
Dialogue: 0,0:34:20.23,0:34:21.75,Default,,0,0,0,,when people have deeply
Dialogue: 0,0:34:21.75,0:34:23.81,Default,,0,0,0,,ingrained notions about how a
Dialogue: 0,0:34:23.81,0:34:25.42,Default,,0,0,0,,system works, and how they
Dialogue: 0,0:34:25.42,0:34:26.18,Default,,0,0,0,,interact with it.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:27.58,0:34:29.97,Default,,0,0,0,,This is a big issue in app
Dialogue: 0,0:34:29.97,0:34:30.37,Default,,0,0,0,,design.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:31.16,0:34:33.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Trust me, I have been there more
Dialogue: 0,0:34:33.39,0:34:33.84,Default,,0,0,0,,than once.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:34.75,0:34:36.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Trying to get people to change
Dialogue: 0,0:34:36.58,0:34:38.15,Default,,0,0,0,,their mental model of how your
Dialogue: 0,0:34:38.15,0:34:39.61,Default,,0,0,0,,app works is risky.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:40.38,0:34:42.23,Default,,0,0,0,,This becomes even more true the
Dialogue: 0,0:34:42.23,0:34:43.74,Default,,0,0,0,,more familiar people are with
Dialogue: 0,0:34:43.79,0:34:44.43,Default,,0,0,0,,your app.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:45.37,0:34:46.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Changes to any long-lived
Dialogue: 0,0:34:46.78,0:34:49.15,Default,,0,0,0,,existing product will inevitably
Dialogue: 0,0:34:49.15,0:34:50.81,Default,,0,0,0,,be hard for people to adjust to.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:50.81,0:34:52.38,Default,,0,0,0,,It really doesn't matter how
Dialogue: 0,0:34:52.38,0:34:54.29,Default,,0,0,0,,good or how necessary those
Dialogue: 0,0:34:54.29,0:34:55.04,Default,,0,0,0,,changes may be.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:55.44,0:34:57.90,Default,,0,0,0,,When considering big changes to
Dialogue: 0,0:34:57.90,0:34:59.89,Default,,0,0,0,,an existing app, you have to be
Dialogue: 0,0:34:59.89,0:35:02.46,Default,,0,0,0,,100 percent positive that those
Dialogue: 0,0:35:02.46,0:35:04.20,Default,,0,0,0,,changes will lead to clear wins
Dialogue: 0,0:35:04.26,0:35:05.77,Default,,0,0,0,,for the people who currently use
Dialogue: 0,0:35:05.77,0:35:06.38,Default,,0,0,0,,your app.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:06.88,0:35:08.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Making changes just for the sake
Dialogue: 0,0:35:08.71,0:35:10.10,Default,,0,0,0,,of it is not a good
Dialogue: 0,0:35:10.10,0:35:10.97,Default,,0,0,0,,justification.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:11.67,0:35:12.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Go carefully.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:12.69,0:35:13.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Test your design.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:13.97,0:35:15.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Prove to yourself beyond a
Dialogue: 0,0:35:15.23,0:35:17.29,Default,,0,0,0,,shadow of a doubt that your
Dialogue: 0,0:35:17.29,0:35:19.09,Default,,0,0,0,,innovations are objectively
Dialogue: 0,0:35:19.09,0:35:19.45,Default,,0,0,0,,better.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:20.57,0:35:22.70,Default,,0,0,0,,If you can do that, then it's
Dialogue: 0,0:35:22.70,0:35:23.55,Default,,0,0,0,,good to push through.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:23.94,0:35:24.94,Default,,0,0,0,,People will come around
Dialogue: 0,0:35:25.11,0:35:25.61,Default,,0,0,0,,eventually.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:27.19,0:35:30.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay. So it's time to start
Dialogue: 0,0:35:30.12,0:35:31.21,Default,,0,0,0,,getting ready for dinner.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:31.63,0:35:33.02,Default,,0,0,0,,So you decide to throw on that
Dialogue: 0,0:35:33.11,0:35:35.67,Default,,0,0,0,,dope new Aloha shirt, and you
Dialogue: 0,0:35:35.67,0:35:37.15,Default,,0,0,0,,exit the bathroom and you turn
Dialogue: 0,0:35:37.15,0:35:38.73,Default,,0,0,0,,off the lights by flipping a
Dialogue: 0,0:35:38.73,0:35:39.17,Default,,0,0,0,,switch.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:39.86,0:35:41.23,Default,,0,0,0,,The sun is setting outside.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:41.23,0:35:43.59,Default,,0,0,0,,It is a bit dark, so you turn on
Dialogue: 0,0:35:43.59,0:35:44.56,Default,,0,0,0,,a light in the hallway.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:45.37,0:35:46.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Then you walk over to the
Dialogue: 0,0:35:46.70,0:35:48.60,Default,,0,0,0,,bedroom and you flip on another
Dialogue: 0,0:35:48.60,0:35:50.83,Default,,0,0,0,,couple of light switches to turn
Dialogue: 0,0:35:50.83,0:35:52.04,Default,,0,0,0,,the lights on out there.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:52.95,0:35:54.72,Default,,0,0,0,,This, in a nutshell, is the
Dialogue: 0,0:35:54.72,0:35:56.99,Default,,0,0,0,,design principle of proximity.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:58.15,0:36:00.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Proximity is about the distance
Dialogue: 0,0:36:00.33,0:36:02.51,Default,,0,0,0,,between a control and the object
Dialogue: 0,0:36:02.64,0:36:03.55,Default,,0,0,0,,that it affects.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:04.53,0:36:06.51,Default,,0,0,0,,The closer a control is to that
Dialogue: 0,0:36:06.51,0:36:08.95,Default,,0,0,0,,object, the more we assume there
Dialogue: 0,0:36:08.99,0:36:11.16,Default,,0,0,0,,to be a connection between the
Dialogue: 0,0:36:11.16,0:36:11.45,Default,,0,0,0,,two.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:12.64,0:36:14.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Of course the bathroom light
Dialogue: 0,0:36:14.08,0:36:15.07,Default,,0,0,0,,switch is in the bathroom.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:15.42,0:36:16.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Of course the hallway light
Dialogue: 0,0:36:16.64,0:36:17.49,Default,,0,0,0,,switch is in the hallway.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:17.75,0:36:19.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Of course the bedroom light
Dialogue: 0,0:36:19.13,0:36:21.70,Default,,0,0,0,,switch is in the bedroom.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:21.81,0:36:23.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Greater proximity also makes
Dialogue: 0,0:36:23.51,0:36:24.58,Default,,0,0,0,,ergonomic sense.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:24.90,0:36:26.36,Default,,0,0,0,,In general, the closer you are
Dialogue: 0,0:36:26.36,0:36:27.57,Default,,0,0,0,,to an object or region of
Dialogue: 0,0:36:27.57,0:36:29.17,Default,,0,0,0,,interest, the more likely you
Dialogue: 0,0:36:29.17,0:36:31.09,Default,,0,0,0,,are to want to interact with it
Dialogue: 0,0:36:31.39,0:36:32.30,Default,,0,0,0,,and control it.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:32.77,0:36:33.95,Default,,0,0,0,,People think to turn on the
Dialogue: 0,0:36:33.95,0:36:35.14,Default,,0,0,0,,bathroom light when they walk
Dialogue: 0,0:36:35.14,0:36:35.89,Default,,0,0,0,,into the bathroom.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:35.89,0:36:37.06,Default,,0,0,0,,So, by putting the light switch
Dialogue: 0,0:36:37.11,0:36:38.79,Default,,0,0,0,,right by the door, it is within
Dialogue: 0,0:36:38.79,0:36:40.14,Default,,0,0,0,,arm's reach when they need it
Dialogue: 0,0:36:40.14,0:36:40.61,Default,,0,0,0,,most.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:42.08,0:36:44.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Proximity is also useful for
Dialogue: 0,0:36:44.12,0:36:46.08,Default,,0,0,0,,expressing relationships between
Dialogue: 0,0:36:46.08,0:36:46.61,Default,,0,0,0,,controls.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:47.16,0:36:48.44,Default,,0,0,0,,So, for example, if you see a
Dialogue: 0,0:36:48.44,0:36:50.53,Default,,0,0,0,,set of switches on the wall, and
Dialogue: 0,0:36:50.53,0:36:51.85,Default,,0,0,0,,you know that one of them
Dialogue: 0,0:36:51.90,0:36:54.03,Default,,0,0,0,,controls lights, then it's
Dialogue: 0,0:36:54.03,0:36:55.55,Default,,0,0,0,,reasonable for you to assume
Dialogue: 0,0:36:55.55,0:36:57.37,Default,,0,0,0,,that every switch is a light
Dialogue: 0,0:36:57.37,0:36:57.76,Default,,0,0,0,,switch.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:58.77,0:37:00.17,Default,,0,0,0,,If one of them controls the
Dialogue: 0,0:37:00.17,0:37:02.04,Default,,0,0,0,,shade, then it would be better
Dialogue: 0,0:37:02.04,0:37:03.45,Default,,0,0,0,,to separate it out from the
Dialogue: 0,0:37:03.45,0:37:03.83,Default,,0,0,0,,rest.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:04.77,0:37:06.66,Default,,0,0,0,,This configuration makes it
Dialogue: 0,0:37:06.66,0:37:08.34,Default,,0,0,0,,easier for people to remember
Dialogue: 0,0:37:08.34,0:37:10.02,Default,,0,0,0,,which switch controls the shade,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:10.38,0:37:11.96,Default,,0,0,0,,and which ones control the
Dialogue: 0,0:37:11.96,0:37:12.39,Default,,0,0,0,,lights.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:13.85,0:37:15.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay, now it's probably worth
Dialogue: 0,0:37:15.80,0:37:17.55,Default,,0,0,0,,pointing out right now that we
Dialogue: 0,0:37:17.55,0:37:19.21,Default,,0,0,0,,have a very special name for
Dialogue: 0,0:37:19.21,0:37:21.07,Default,,0,0,0,,this configuration, this
Dialogue: 0,0:37:21.07,0:37:22.28,Default,,0,0,0,,arrangement here on the right.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:22.92,0:37:24.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Does anyone care to guess what
Dialogue: 0,0:37:24.08,0:37:24.53,Default,,0,0,0,,it is?
Dialogue: 0,0:37:25.19,0:37:26.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Just go ahead and shout it out.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:27.30,0:37:28.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay, you're smart, you're not
Dialogue: 0,0:37:28.23,0:37:28.85,Default,,0,0,0,,going to fall for it.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:28.97,0:37:31.03,Default,,0,0,0,,I just tried to get you.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:31.03,0:37:32.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay, if you guessed in your
Dialogue: 0,0:37:32.34,0:37:34.04,Default,,0,0,0,,mind that it is a group, then
Dialogue: 0,0:37:34.04,0:37:35.26,Default,,0,0,0,,you win a prize.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:35.26,0:37:36.55,Default,,0,0,0,,It is a trip to Hawaii.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:37.47,0:37:39.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Grouping is a very fundamental
Dialogue: 0,0:37:39.48,0:37:40.80,Default,,0,0,0,,and significant design
Dialogue: 0,0:37:40.80,0:37:41.38,Default,,0,0,0,,principle.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:42.02,0:37:43.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Grouping helps people to
Dialogue: 0,0:37:43.08,0:37:44.68,Default,,0,0,0,,understand the relationships
Dialogue: 0,0:37:44.72,0:37:46.66,Default,,0,0,0,,between elements, and it is key
Dialogue: 0,0:37:46.66,0:37:48.31,Default,,0,0,0,,for giving a design structure.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:49.05,0:37:50.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, while we all understand
Dialogue: 0,0:37:50.66,0:37:52.81,Default,,0,0,0,,this, many apps don't
Dialogue: 0,0:37:52.81,0:37:54.20,Default,,0,0,0,,effectively use grouping.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:54.31,0:37:55.85,Default,,0,0,0,,It can be easy to overlook.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:57.25,0:37:58.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, let's take a look at a
Dialogue: 0,0:37:58.59,0:38:00.16,Default,,0,0,0,,couple of examples of how
Dialogue: 0,0:38:00.16,0:38:02.03,Default,,0,0,0,,proximity and grouping can be
Dialogue: 0,0:38:02.03,0:38:04.64,Default,,0,0,0,,used to structure a design, and
Dialogue: 0,0:38:04.64,0:38:06.55,Default,,0,0,0,,establish relationships between
Dialogue: 0,0:38:06.55,0:38:08.54,Default,,0,0,0,,controls and the objects or
Dialogue: 0,0:38:08.54,0:38:09.67,Default,,0,0,0,,views that they affect.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:10.82,0:38:13.27,Default,,0,0,0,,And keynote, proximity helps us
Dialogue: 0,0:38:13.27,0:38:16.08,Default,,0,0,0,,to associate the view menu with
Dialogue: 0,0:38:16.43,0:38:18.01,Default,,0,0,0,,the slide navigator and the
Dialogue: 0,0:38:18.01,0:38:18.71,Default,,0,0,0,,canvas area.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:18.93,0:38:20.58,Default,,0,0,0,,The objects that it affects.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:21.78,0:38:23.09,Default,,0,0,0,,The object creation tools are
Dialogue: 0,0:38:23.09,0:38:23.86,Default,,0,0,0,,positioned right above the
Dialogue: 0,0:38:23.86,0:38:25.48,Default,,0,0,0,,canvas, which is where those
Dialogue: 0,0:38:25.48,0:38:26.65,Default,,0,0,0,,objects go.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:27.20,0:38:29.49,Default,,0,0,0,,The anime format and document
Dialogue: 0,0:38:29.49,0:38:31.46,Default,,0,0,0,,visibility switches are located
Dialogue: 0,0:38:31.46,0:38:32.74,Default,,0,0,0,,just above where those panels
Dialogue: 0,0:38:32.74,0:38:33.44,Default,,0,0,0,,get displayed.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:34.63,0:38:36.52,Default,,0,0,0,,In Sketch, you can see how
Dialogue: 0,0:38:36.61,0:38:38.31,Default,,0,0,0,,grouping is used to cluster
Dialogue: 0,0:38:38.31,0:38:39.61,Default,,0,0,0,,related controls with each
Dialogue: 0,0:38:39.61,0:38:41.42,Default,,0,0,0,,other, like the grouping
Dialogue: 0,0:38:41.42,0:38:42.02,Default,,0,0,0,,controls.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:42.64,0:38:44.08,Default,,0,0,0,,The Transform and Edit tools.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:44.71,0:38:46.36,Default,,0,0,0,,The Pathfinding operations.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:47.00,0:38:48.65,Default,,0,0,0,,And the Layer Ordering actions.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:50.28,0:38:52.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, I just shared two Mac apps,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:52.58,0:38:54.21,Default,,0,0,0,,and the need for proximity and
Dialogue: 0,0:38:54.21,0:38:55.89,Default,,0,0,0,,grouping is definitely higher
Dialogue: 0,0:38:56.16,0:38:57.69,Default,,0,0,0,,the larger your interface is,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:58.19,0:39:00.09,Default,,0,0,0,,but the principles are still
Dialogue: 0,0:39:00.09,0:39:01.90,Default,,0,0,0,,crucial for smaller screens,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:02.19,0:39:04.65,Default,,0,0,0,,like iPads and iPhones, and even
Dialogue: 0,0:39:04.65,0:39:05.38,Default,,0,0,0,,the Apple Watch.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:06.48,0:39:08.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay, so I think there is time
Dialogue: 0,0:39:08.83,0:39:10.43,Default,,0,0,0,,to learn about just one more
Dialogue: 0,0:39:10.43,0:39:11.76,Default,,0,0,0,,design principle before we head
Dialogue: 0,0:39:11.76,0:39:12.99,Default,,0,0,0,,downstairs to the hotel
Dialogue: 0,0:39:12.99,0:39:14.66,Default,,0,0,0,,restaurant and grab some dinner.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:15.74,0:39:17.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's go back to that Shade
Dialogue: 0,0:39:17.02,0:39:18.00,Default,,0,0,0,,control again.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:18.93,0:39:20.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, looking at this control, do
Dialogue: 0,0:39:20.76,0:39:22.41,Default,,0,0,0,,you suppose that the Shade is
Dialogue: 0,0:39:22.46,0:39:24.31,Default,,0,0,0,,open or closed?
Dialogue: 0,0:39:25.32,0:39:25.98,Default,,0,0,0,,How about now?
Dialogue: 0,0:39:26.78,0:39:28.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Just show of hands here.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:28.49,0:39:29.72,Default,,0,0,0,,How many people think that it is
Dialogue: 0,0:39:29.72,0:39:30.29,Default,,0,0,0,,closed?
Dialogue: 0,0:39:31.50,0:39:34.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay, okay, and how many of you
Dialogue: 0,0:39:34.31,0:39:35.36,Default,,0,0,0,,think that it is open?
Dialogue: 0,0:39:35.36,0:39:38.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, you guys are a really
Dialogue: 0,0:39:38.60,0:39:39.78,Default,,0,0,0,,smart group of people.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:39.78,0:39:40.82,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:40.82,0:39:43.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Mapping is how you know that it
Dialogue: 0,0:39:43.83,0:39:44.34,Default,,0,0,0,,is closed.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:45.07,0:39:46.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Mapping is about designing
Dialogue: 0,0:39:46.38,0:39:48.56,Default,,0,0,0,,controls to resemble the objects
Dialogue: 0,0:39:48.63,0:39:49.37,Default,,0,0,0,,that they affect.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:50.60,0:39:52.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Shades go up, and shades go
Dialogue: 0,0:39:52.52,0:39:52.89,Default,,0,0,0,,down.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:53.57,0:39:54.90,Default,,0,0,0,,So it makes sense to use a
Dialogue: 0,0:39:54.90,0:39:57.00,Default,,0,0,0,,control that mirrors that up and
Dialogue: 0,0:39:57.00,0:39:57.90,Default,,0,0,0,,down movement.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:59.33,0:40:01.13,Default,,0,0,0,,There is no ambiguity about how
Dialogue: 0,0:40:01.13,0:40:02.98,Default,,0,0,0,,to raise or lower the shade.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:04.29,0:40:05.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Mapping also relates to how
Dialogue: 0,0:40:05.90,0:40:07.71,Default,,0,0,0,,controls are arranged relative
Dialogue: 0,0:40:07.76,0:40:08.36,Default,,0,0,0,,to each other.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:09.11,0:40:10.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Their order should resemble the
Dialogue: 0,0:40:10.53,0:40:12.31,Default,,0,0,0,,configuration of the objects
Dialogue: 0,0:40:12.31,0:40:12.97,Default,,0,0,0,,that they affect.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:13.77,0:40:15.62,Default,,0,0,0,,So let's say that these light
Dialogue: 0,0:40:15.62,0:40:17.50,Default,,0,0,0,,switches control three sets of
Dialogue: 0,0:40:17.50,0:40:18.86,Default,,0,0,0,,ceiling lights in the bedroom.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:20.23,0:40:21.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Good mapping involves arranging
Dialogue: 0,0:40:21.87,0:40:23.11,Default,,0,0,0,,the switches to mirror the
Dialogue: 0,0:40:23.11,0:40:24.75,Default,,0,0,0,,layout of those lights.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:26.04,0:40:28.08,Default,,0,0,0,,By focusing on mapping, it is so
Dialogue: 0,0:40:28.08,0:40:29.90,Default,,0,0,0,,much easier to make choices
Dialogue: 0,0:40:30.24,0:40:31.41,Default,,0,0,0,,about where to position
Dialogue: 0,0:40:31.41,0:40:33.92,Default,,0,0,0,,controls, how to order them, and
Dialogue: 0,0:40:33.92,0:40:35.82,Default,,0,0,0,,even which controls to use.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:36.46,0:40:37.61,Default,,0,0,0,,I mean, we've all seen light
Dialogue: 0,0:40:37.64,0:40:38.93,Default,,0,0,0,,switches that look like this.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:40.32,0:40:41.88,Default,,0,0,0,,You will often find labels when
Dialogue: 0,0:40:41.88,0:40:43.40,Default,,0,0,0,,mapping is unclear.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:43.40,0:40:44.81,Default,,0,0,0,,It is a telltale sign.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:45.44,0:40:47.12,Default,,0,0,0,,But it is not a particularly
Dialogue: 0,0:40:47.12,0:40:47.98,Default,,0,0,0,,good solution.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:48.57,0:40:49.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Reading takes time, and it
Dialogue: 0,0:40:49.78,0:40:51.11,Default,,0,0,0,,doesn't help people to memorize
Dialogue: 0,0:40:51.15,0:40:53.05,Default,,0,0,0,,the location of controls or how
Dialogue: 0,0:40:53.05,0:40:54.64,Default,,0,0,0,,they should interact with them.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:55.74,0:40:56.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, in the context of
Dialogue: 0,0:40:56.57,0:40:57.80,Default,,0,0,0,,interface, adjusting a
Dialogue: 0,0:40:57.80,0:40:59.36,Default,,0,0,0,,horizontal property is much more
Dialogue: 0,0:40:59.36,0:41:01.17,Default,,0,0,0,,intuitive with the horizontal
Dialogue: 0,0:41:01.17,0:41:01.63,Default,,0,0,0,,slider.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:02.46,0:41:03.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Similarly, using a dial for
Dialogue: 0,0:41:03.96,0:41:05.70,Default,,0,0,0,,adjusting rotation is much
Dialogue: 0,0:41:05.70,0:41:07.08,Default,,0,0,0,,better than a slider or a
Dialogue: 0,0:41:07.08,0:41:07.55,Default,,0,0,0,,stepper.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:08.36,0:41:11.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Of course, the best mapping is
Dialogue: 0,0:41:11.19,0:41:12.63,Default,,0,0,0,,the most direct mapping.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:13.28,0:41:14.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Providing the ability for people
Dialogue: 0,0:41:14.79,0:41:16.67,Default,,0,0,0,,to directly manipulate an object
Dialogue: 0,0:41:16.74,0:41:17.93,Default,,0,0,0,,is more straightforward, it's
Dialogue: 0,0:41:17.93,0:41:19.42,Default,,0,0,0,,more intuitive, and precise.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:19.85,0:41:21.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Whether that is with a pointer
Dialogue: 0,0:41:21.03,0:41:24.63,Default,,0,0,0,,on macOS, or Gestures on iOS.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:25.90,0:41:28.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay, so enough about light
Dialogue: 0,0:41:28.09,0:41:28.53,Default,,0,0,0,,switches.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:28.53,0:41:30.69,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know about you, but I am
Dialogue: 0,0:41:30.69,0:41:32.45,Default,,0,0,0,,starving, and it is time to head
Dialogue: 0,0:41:32.45,0:41:34.60,Default,,0,0,0,,downstairs and get some dinner.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:35.50,0:41:36.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, we all meet up in the lobby
Dialogue: 0,0:41:36.76,0:41:38.08,Default,,0,0,0,,and we make our way over to the
Dialogue: 0,0:41:38.08,0:41:39.96,Default,,0,0,0,,restaurant, and as you sit down
Dialogue: 0,0:41:39.96,0:41:41.49,Default,,0,0,0,,at the table, you see in front
Dialogue: 0,0:41:41.49,0:41:43.37,Default,,0,0,0,,of you an empty dinner plate.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:44.67,0:41:46.89,Default,,0,0,0,,What can you do with this dinner
Dialogue: 0,0:41:46.92,0:41:47.13,Default,,0,0,0,,plate?
Dialogue: 0,0:41:47.73,0:41:50.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, of course, you can put
Dialogue: 0,0:41:50.63,0:41:53.08,Default,,0,0,0,,food on it, #putfoodonit
Dialogue: 0,0:41:53.08,0:41:54.30,Default,,0,0,0,,[laughter].
Dialogue: 0,0:41:54.30,0:41:56.47,Default,,0,0,0,,But you can do all sorts of
Dialogue: 0,0:41:56.47,0:41:57.55,Default,,0,0,0,,other stuff too.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:58.48,0:41:59.92,Default,,0,0,0,,The plate is smooth, so it looks
Dialogue: 0,0:41:59.92,0:42:01.01,Default,,0,0,0,,like it is easy to rotate and
Dialogue: 0,0:42:01.01,0:42:01.68,Default,,0,0,0,,slide around.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:02.68,0:42:04.07,Default,,0,0,0,,There is a nice little gap along
Dialogue: 0,0:42:04.07,0:42:05.44,Default,,0,0,0,,the edge, so it looks easy to
Dialogue: 0,0:42:05.44,0:42:06.80,Default,,0,0,0,,grab and lift up.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:07.72,0:42:09.26,Default,,0,0,0,,It looks like a Frisbee, so you
Dialogue: 0,0:42:09.26,0:42:11.55,Default,,0,0,0,,consider how far you can make it
Dialogue: 0,0:42:12.52,0:42:12.60,Default,,0,0,0,,go.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:12.81,0:42:14.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Or maybe not.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:14.89,0:42:16.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Our notions about how we
Dialogue: 0,0:42:16.42,0:42:18.84,Default,,0,0,0,,interact with this plate are
Dialogue: 0,0:42:18.84,0:42:20.25,Default,,0,0,0,,called affordances.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:21.50,0:42:23.19,Default,,0,0,0,,In other words, a plate's
Dialogue: 0,0:42:23.19,0:42:24.97,Default,,0,0,0,,physical characteristics provide
Dialogue: 0,0:42:25.06,0:42:27.88,Default,,0,0,0,,visual and tactile cues about
Dialogue: 0,0:42:27.88,0:42:29.36,Default,,0,0,0,,what interactions the plate
Dialogue: 0,0:42:29.36,0:42:30.63,Default,,0,0,0,,afford to us.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:31.60,0:42:32.58,Default,,0,0,0,,A plate's physical
Dialogue: 0,0:42:32.58,0:42:34.22,Default,,0,0,0,,characteristics make certain
Dialogue: 0,0:42:34.22,0:42:36.02,Default,,0,0,0,,actions seem possible, and
Dialogue: 0,0:42:36.02,0:42:37.29,Default,,0,0,0,,others less possible.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:37.98,0:42:38.90,Default,,0,0,0,,We look at the plate, and we
Dialogue: 0,0:42:38.90,0:42:39.92,Default,,0,0,0,,think, I am going to put food
Dialogue: 0,0:42:39.92,0:42:40.89,Default,,0,0,0,,onto this object.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:41.38,0:42:42.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Or, we might also think, I'm
Dialogue: 0,0:42:42.90,0:42:44.26,Default,,0,0,0,,going to use this object to
Dialogue: 0,0:42:44.30,0:42:45.84,Default,,0,0,0,,transport my food to a different
Dialogue: 0,0:42:45.84,0:42:46.36,Default,,0,0,0,,location.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:47.08,0:42:48.23,Default,,0,0,0,,We don't look at this plate and
Dialogue: 0,0:42:48.23,0:42:49.54,Default,,0,0,0,,think, I'm going to use it for
Dialogue: 0,0:42:49.54,0:42:50.39,Default,,0,0,0,,drinking water.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:51.44,0:42:53.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Affordance is not an attribute
Dialogue: 0,0:42:53.37,0:42:54.65,Default,,0,0,0,,of the object itself.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:55.37,0:42:56.86,Default,,0,0,0,,It is more about the
Dialogue: 0,0:42:56.86,0:42:58.73,Default,,0,0,0,,relationship that individuals
Dialogue: 0,0:42:58.87,0:42:59.95,Default,,0,0,0,,have to an object.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:00.74,0:43:03.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Affordance varies based on one's
Dialogue: 0,0:43:03.86,0:43:05.19,Default,,0,0,0,,physical abilities.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:05.39,0:43:07.25,Default,,0,0,0,,So, therefore, affordance varies
Dialogue: 0,0:43:07.25,0:43:08.44,Default,,0,0,0,,from person to person.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:09.13,0:43:10.64,Default,,0,0,0,,So, for example, this is kind of
Dialogue: 0,0:43:10.64,0:43:11.36,Default,,0,0,0,,an extreme one.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:12.31,0:43:13.85,Default,,0,0,0,,A Frisbee affords me with a
Dialogue: 0,0:43:13.85,0:43:15.49,Default,,0,0,0,,possibility of catching and
Dialogue: 0,0:43:15.49,0:43:15.98,Default,,0,0,0,,throwing.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:16.61,0:43:18.36,Default,,0,0,0,,For my dog, a Frisbee affords
Dialogue: 0,0:43:18.36,0:43:20.28,Default,,0,0,0,,the ability of catching, but not
Dialogue: 0,0:43:20.28,0:43:20.71,Default,,0,0,0,,throwing.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:21.29,0:43:23.56,Default,,0,0,0,,A plate affords me with the
Dialogue: 0,0:43:23.56,0:43:25.47,Default,,0,0,0,,ability of eating food off of
Dialogue: 0,0:43:26.19,0:43:26.26,Default,,0,0,0,,it.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:26.64,0:43:28.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Interestingly, my dog perceives
Dialogue: 0,0:43:28.29,0:43:29.39,Default,,0,0,0,,the very same affordance.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:30.68,0:43:32.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, because affordance is
Dialogue: 0,0:43:32.45,0:43:34.48,Default,,0,0,0,,subjective, one person can
Dialogue: 0,0:43:34.48,0:43:35.57,Default,,0,0,0,,perceive an affordance when
Dialogue: 0,0:43:35.57,0:43:36.39,Default,,0,0,0,,another does not.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:36.96,0:43:38.13,Default,,0,0,0,,People are more likely to
Dialogue: 0,0:43:38.13,0:43:39.21,Default,,0,0,0,,perceive an affordance when it
Dialogue: 0,0:43:39.21,0:43:40.78,Default,,0,0,0,,is related to an action that
Dialogue: 0,0:43:40.78,0:43:42.13,Default,,0,0,0,,they are more likely to take.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:42.92,0:43:45.52,Default,,0,0,0,,So, for instance, I could use a
Dialogue: 0,0:43:45.52,0:43:47.26,Default,,0,0,0,,plate as a saucer, and it would
Dialogue: 0,0:43:47.26,0:43:48.70,Default,,0,0,0,,make a really great saucer.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:48.77,0:43:50.24,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't think I would get any
Dialogue: 0,0:43:50.52,0:43:53.39,Default,,0,0,0,,argument from you guys, but this
Dialogue: 0,0:43:53.39,0:43:55.12,Default,,0,0,0,,is an unlikely action to take,
Dialogue: 0,0:43:55.12,0:43:56.88,Default,,0,0,0,,so I wouldn't readily perceive a
Dialogue: 0,0:43:56.88,0:43:58.33,Default,,0,0,0,,plate's glass-putting
Dialogue: 0,0:43:58.33,0:44:00.57,Default,,0,0,0,,affordance, whereas I'm very
Dialogue: 0,0:44:00.57,0:44:01.77,Default,,0,0,0,,likely to put food on it.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:02.07,0:44:03.79,Default,,0,0,0,,So I readily perceive the
Dialogue: 0,0:44:03.79,0:44:05.34,Default,,0,0,0,,plate's food-putting affordance.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:06.64,0:44:08.74,Default,,0,0,0,,You perceive affordances with
Dialogue: 0,0:44:08.74,0:44:10.27,Default,,0,0,0,,every environment and every
Dialogue: 0,0:44:10.27,0:44:11.60,Default,,0,0,0,,object that you have ever
Dialogue: 0,0:44:11.60,0:44:12.43,Default,,0,0,0,,interacted with.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:13.08,0:44:14.17,Default,,0,0,0,,When you walked into the
Dialogue: 0,0:44:14.17,0:44:16.28,Default,,0,0,0,,restaurant, you passed through a
Dialogue: 0,0:44:16.28,0:44:17.57,Default,,0,0,0,,door that afforded you the
Dialogue: 0,0:44:17.57,0:44:18.92,Default,,0,0,0,,ability of passage.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:19.48,0:44:21.10,Default,,0,0,0,,The door is human-sized, so you
Dialogue: 0,0:44:21.10,0:44:22.77,Default,,0,0,0,,can imagine your body moving
Dialogue: 0,0:44:22.82,0:44:24.04,Default,,0,0,0,,through it unobstructed.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:24.61,0:44:26.23,Default,,0,0,0,,There was a continuous grounds
Dialogue: 0,0:44:26.27,0:44:27.75,Default,,0,0,0,,plane, so you can imagine
Dialogue: 0,0:44:27.75,0:44:29.06,Default,,0,0,0,,yourself walking along it,
Dialogue: 0,0:44:29.06,0:44:30.53,Default,,0,0,0,,without stumbling, tripping.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:31.68,0:44:32.97,Default,,0,0,0,,The chair that you sat in
Dialogue: 0,0:44:33.03,0:44:34.89,Default,,0,0,0,,affords the ability for sitting.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:35.71,0:44:37.14,Default,,0,0,0,,The table in front of you
Dialogue: 0,0:44:37.14,0:44:38.62,Default,,0,0,0,,affords the ability of putting
Dialogue: 0,0:44:38.62,0:44:39.70,Default,,0,0,0,,objects onto it.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:40.64,0:44:42.29,Default,,0,0,0,,The ground below your feet
Dialogue: 0,0:44:42.29,0:44:44.18,Default,,0,0,0,,affords the ability for resting
Dialogue: 0,0:44:44.18,0:44:44.56,Default,,0,0,0,,your feet.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:45.84,0:44:47.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Manufactured objects include
Dialogue: 0,0:44:47.90,0:44:49.98,Default,,0,0,0,,cues to evoke affordances.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:51.28,0:44:52.26,Default,,0,0,0,,They let people know what
Dialogue: 0,0:44:52.26,0:44:54.87,Default,,0,0,0,,actions are possible, and the
Dialogue: 0,0:44:54.87,0:44:57.00,Default,,0,0,0,,obviousness and visibility of
Dialogue: 0,0:44:57.00,0:44:58.53,Default,,0,0,0,,those cues helps people to know
Dialogue: 0,0:44:58.53,0:45:00.85,Default,,0,0,0,,the correct or the intended ways
Dialogue: 0,0:45:00.85,0:45:02.85,Default,,0,0,0,,of interacting, and the same
Dialogue: 0,0:45:02.85,0:45:04.10,Default,,0,0,0,,should be true for apps.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:05.38,0:45:07.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Sliders afford dragging a knob
Dialogue: 0,0:45:07.18,0:45:08.44,Default,,0,0,0,,along a track.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:09.02,0:45:10.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Dials afford rotating.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:11.40,0:45:13.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Buttons afford tapping, and
Dialogue: 0,0:45:13.55,0:45:13.92,Default,,0,0,0,,clicking.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:14.96,0:45:16.41,Default,,0,0,0,,In each of these examples,
Dialogue: 0,0:45:16.73,0:45:18.33,Default,,0,0,0,,affordance is communicated with
Dialogue: 0,0:45:18.36,0:45:19.77,Default,,0,0,0,,maximum efficiency.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:20.33,0:45:22.24,Default,,0,0,0,,In fact, over time, we are all
Dialogue: 0,0:45:22.24,0:45:23.73,Default,,0,0,0,,becoming more comfortable with
Dialogue: 0,0:45:23.73,0:45:25.10,Default,,0,0,0,,increasing levels of
Dialogue: 0,0:45:25.10,0:45:25.93,Default,,0,0,0,,abstraction.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:26.61,0:45:28.19,Default,,0,0,0,,The button, after all, is just a
Dialogue: 0,0:45:28.19,0:45:30.39,Default,,0,0,0,,highly abstracted version of a
Dialogue: 0,0:45:30.39,0:45:32.59,Default,,0,0,0,,physical, real-world button.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:33.56,0:45:35.46,Default,,0,0,0,,All that's necessary to create a
Dialogue: 0,0:45:35.46,0:45:36.76,Default,,0,0,0,,strong connection between the
Dialogue: 0,0:45:36.76,0:45:38.18,Default,,0,0,0,,two are the rounding of the
Dialogue: 0,0:45:38.18,0:45:38.82,Default,,0,0,0,,corners.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:39.49,0:45:41.01,Default,,0,0,0,,A subtle drop shadow around the
Dialogue: 0,0:45:41.01,0:45:42.60,Default,,0,0,0,,slider knob separates it from
Dialogue: 0,0:45:42.60,0:45:43.73,Default,,0,0,0,,the track that it is positioned
Dialogue: 0,0:45:43.73,0:45:45.34,Default,,0,0,0,,over, and this separation
Dialogue: 0,0:45:45.34,0:45:46.68,Default,,0,0,0,,suggests that it can be moved
Dialogue: 0,0:45:46.71,0:45:47.51,Default,,0,0,0,,independently.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:48.19,0:45:49.58,Default,,0,0,0,,And even that visual cue might
Dialogue: 0,0:45:49.58,0:45:51.32,Default,,0,0,0,,not be completely necessary.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:51.75,0:45:53.18,Default,,0,0,0,,For most people, simply seeing a
Dialogue: 0,0:45:53.18,0:45:54.69,Default,,0,0,0,,filled-in circle over a line is
Dialogue: 0,0:45:54.69,0:45:56.57,Default,,0,0,0,,all that is needed to express a
Dialogue: 0,0:45:56.57,0:45:57.68,Default,,0,0,0,,sliding affordance.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:59.06,0:46:00.24,Default,,0,0,0,,And sometimes affordance is
Dialogue: 0,0:46:00.24,0:46:01.89,Default,,0,0,0,,communicated using animation.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:02.41,0:46:03.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Tapping on the Weather app, we
Dialogue: 0,0:46:04.03,0:46:05.97,Default,,0,0,0,,see it slide up a little bit.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:05.97,0:46:07.46,Default,,0,0,0,,This suggests the possibility
Dialogue: 0,0:46:07.46,0:46:09.19,Default,,0,0,0,,that the content areas can be
Dialogue: 0,0:46:09.19,0:46:09.74,Default,,0,0,0,,scrolled.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:10.59,0:46:14.51,Default,,0,0,0,,And sure enough, they can.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:14.70,0:46:16.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Regardless of the exact
Dialogue: 0,0:46:16.07,0:46:17.50,Default,,0,0,0,,technique that you use, your
Dialogue: 0,0:46:17.62,0:46:19.43,Default,,0,0,0,,app's interface must make clear
Dialogue: 0,0:46:19.43,0:46:21.14,Default,,0,0,0,,what action possibilities it
Dialogue: 0,0:46:21.14,0:46:21.64,Default,,0,0,0,,affords.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:22.42,0:46:24.20,Default,,0,0,0,,If not, people won't know how to
Dialogue: 0,0:46:24.20,0:46:25.52,Default,,0,0,0,,properly interact with it.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:26.03,0:46:27.01,Default,,0,0,0,,They'll interact in ways that
Dialogue: 0,0:46:27.01,0:46:28.36,Default,,0,0,0,,your app doesn't support, and
Dialogue: 0,0:46:28.36,0:46:30.05,Default,,0,0,0,,they'll confuse controls for
Dialogue: 0,0:46:30.05,0:46:31.62,Default,,0,0,0,,non-interactive objects.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:32.57,0:46:35.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay. So, now that we know where
Dialogue: 0,0:46:35.11,0:46:37.09,Default,,0,0,0,,our food is supposed to go, it
Dialogue: 0,0:46:37.12,0:46:37.96,Default,,0,0,0,,is time to order.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:38.85,0:46:39.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, I am thinking about getting
Dialogue: 0,0:46:39.87,0:46:42.47,Default,,0,0,0,,a cheeseburger because they're
Dialogue: 0,0:46:42.47,0:46:44.27,Default,,0,0,0,,delicious, obviously, and when a
Dialogue: 0,0:46:44.27,0:46:45.97,Default,,0,0,0,,waiter comes by to take my
Dialogue: 0,0:46:45.97,0:46:47.86,Default,,0,0,0,,order, I say, "Cheeseburger,
Dialogue: 0,0:46:47.91,0:46:48.20,Default,,0,0,0,,please."
Dialogue: 0,0:46:48.64,0:46:51.07,Default,,0,0,0,,He then asks how I would like it
Dialogue: 0,0:46:51.07,0:46:52.57,Default,,0,0,0,,cooked, and "medium," I say.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:53.36,0:46:54.24,Default,,0,0,0,,He then asks what kind of
Dialogue: 0,0:46:54.24,0:46:55.65,Default,,0,0,0,,cheese, cheddar, Swiss, Jack,
Dialogue: 0,0:46:55.65,0:46:56.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Gruyere, cottage?
Dialogue: 0,0:46:57.25,0:46:58.46,Default,,0,0,0,,"Cheddar," I say.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:59.52,0:47:00.66,Default,,0,0,0,,He then asks whether I would
Dialogue: 0,0:47:00.66,0:47:03.12,Default,,0,0,0,,like bacon, egg, avocado on it?
Dialogue: 0,0:47:03.73,0:47:04.83,Default,,0,0,0,,"None," I say.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:05.02,0:47:06.69,Default,,0,0,0,,I am trying to keep my figure.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:08.19,0:47:09.41,Default,,0,0,0,,He then asks whether I'd like
Dialogue: 0,0:47:09.41,0:47:11.35,Default,,0,0,0,,salad, fries or onion rings.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:12.07,0:47:13.24,Default,,0,0,0,,"Onion rings," I say.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:14.04,0:47:15.51,Default,,0,0,0,,He then asks if I realize that
Dialogue: 0,0:47:15.51,0:47:16.75,Default,,0,0,0,,cheeseburgers and onion rings
Dialogue: 0,0:47:16.75,0:47:18.90,Default,,0,0,0,,are very high in calories, to
Dialogue: 0,0:47:18.90,0:47:20.66,Default,,0,0,0,,which I reply, "Fake news"
Dialogue: 0,0:47:20.66,0:47:21.82,Default,,0,0,0,,[laughter].
Dialogue: 0,0:47:21.82,0:47:32.65,Default,,0,0,0,,This [applause] in a nutshell is
Dialogue: 0,0:47:32.65,0:47:34.21,Default,,0,0,0,,the principle of progressive
Dialogue: 0,0:47:34.21,0:47:34.84,Default,,0,0,0,,disclosure.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:35.66,0:47:37.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Progressive disclosure is a
Dialogue: 0,0:47:37.04,0:47:38.53,Default,,0,0,0,,technique for managing
Dialogue: 0,0:47:38.53,0:47:39.23,Default,,0,0,0,,complexity.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:39.93,0:47:41.55,Default,,0,0,0,,The term is used almost
Dialogue: 0,0:47:41.55,0:47:43.29,Default,,0,0,0,,exclusively in the context of
Dialogue: 0,0:47:43.29,0:47:45.07,Default,,0,0,0,,interaction design, and to my
Dialogue: 0,0:47:45.07,0:47:46.20,Default,,0,0,0,,knowledge, this is the first
Dialogue: 0,0:47:46.20,0:47:48.24,Default,,0,0,0,,time that anyone was dumb enough
Dialogue: 0,0:47:48.24,0:47:49.35,Default,,0,0,0,,to try to use it to describe
Dialogue: 0,0:47:49.35,0:47:50.34,Default,,0,0,0,,ordering a cheeseburger.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:51.35,0:47:52.93,Default,,0,0,0,,The basic idea is this.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:53.76,0:47:55.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Progressive disclosure gradually
Dialogue: 0,0:47:55.72,0:47:57.67,Default,,0,0,0,,eases people from the simple to
Dialogue: 0,0:47:57.67,0:47:58.76,Default,,0,0,0,,the more complex.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:59.86,0:48:01.55,Default,,0,0,0,,And progressive disclosure is
Dialogue: 0,0:48:01.64,0:48:03.28,Default,,0,0,0,,also about hiding away
Dialogue: 0,0:48:03.28,0:48:05.12,Default,,0,0,0,,complexity, so that people can
Dialogue: 0,0:48:05.12,0:48:07.03,Default,,0,0,0,,accomplish basic tasks with
Dialogue: 0,0:48:07.03,0:48:09.18,Default,,0,0,0,,simple and more approachable
Dialogue: 0,0:48:09.18,0:48:09.97,Default,,0,0,0,,interfaces.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:11.03,0:48:12.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Ordering a cheeseburger would be
Dialogue: 0,0:48:12.50,0:48:14.66,Default,,0,0,0,,way more complex and daunting if
Dialogue: 0,0:48:14.66,0:48:15.89,Default,,0,0,0,,you had to consider all of those
Dialogue: 0,0:48:15.89,0:48:16.82,Default,,0,0,0,,options at once.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:17.30,0:48:18.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Customizing your cheeseburger is
Dialogue: 0,0:48:18.86,0:48:20.40,Default,,0,0,0,,way easier when someone steps
Dialogue: 0,0:48:20.40,0:48:22.20,Default,,0,0,0,,you through the process one
Dialogue: 0,0:48:22.20,0:48:23.31,Default,,0,0,0,,decision at a time.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:24.16,0:48:25.51,Default,,0,0,0,,And some choices that you make
Dialogue: 0,0:48:25.51,0:48:27.30,Default,,0,0,0,,early on could make other
Dialogue: 0,0:48:27.30,0:48:28.82,Default,,0,0,0,,choices irrelevant later.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:29.50,0:48:31.78,Default,,0,0,0,,So, for example, if I'd asked
Dialogue: 0,0:48:31.85,0:48:33.58,Default,,0,0,0,,for French fries, the waiter
Dialogue: 0,0:48:33.58,0:48:35.12,Default,,0,0,0,,would have then asked whether I
Dialogue: 0,0:48:35.12,0:48:37.28,Default,,0,0,0,,wanted regular, truffle or
Dialogue: 0,0:48:37.28,0:48:39.14,Default,,0,0,0,,garlic fries, and because I
Dialogue: 0,0:48:39.14,0:48:40.91,Default,,0,0,0,,didn't ask for fries, I don't
Dialogue: 0,0:48:40.91,0:48:42.60,Default,,0,0,0,,really care what kind of French
Dialogue: 0,0:48:42.60,0:48:44.74,Default,,0,0,0,,fries they have, and telling me
Dialogue: 0,0:48:44.74,0:48:46.47,Default,,0,0,0,,about those options would just
Dialogue: 0,0:48:46.47,0:48:48.18,Default,,0,0,0,,be a waste of my time and my
Dialogue: 0,0:48:48.18,0:48:49.65,Default,,0,0,0,,limited mental abilities.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:51.90,0:48:52.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Or would it be?
Dialogue: 0,0:48:53.86,0:48:55.79,Default,,0,0,0,,I mean, I like garlic fries a
Dialogue: 0,0:48:55.79,0:48:58.12,Default,,0,0,0,,lot, and had I known that garlic
Dialogue: 0,0:48:58.12,0:48:59.94,Default,,0,0,0,,fries were on offer, I would
Dialogue: 0,0:48:59.94,0:49:00.67,Default,,0,0,0,,have gotten them.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:01.43,0:49:04.09,Default,,0,0,0,,So herein lies the rub.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:05.59,0:49:06.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Progressive disclosure is a
Dialogue: 0,0:49:06.93,0:49:08.73,Default,,0,0,0,,necessary and helpful technique
Dialogue: 0,0:49:09.04,0:49:11.35,Default,,0,0,0,,for managing complexity and
Dialogue: 0,0:49:11.35,0:49:12.91,Default,,0,0,0,,simplifying decision making.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:13.59,0:49:15.97,Default,,0,0,0,,But the same technique can bury
Dialogue: 0,0:49:15.97,0:49:17.60,Default,,0,0,0,,information or functionality.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:18.33,0:49:19.44,Default,,0,0,0,,So what do you do?
Dialogue: 0,0:49:20.82,0:49:22.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, discussions about how to
Dialogue: 0,0:49:22.13,0:49:23.28,Default,,0,0,0,,properly use progressive
Dialogue: 0,0:49:23.28,0:49:24.87,Default,,0,0,0,,disclosure often come down to
Dialogue: 0,0:49:24.87,0:49:25.78,Default,,0,0,0,,the 80/20 rule.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:26.46,0:49:27.56,Default,,0,0,0,,If you're not familiar, the
Dialogue: 0,0:49:27.56,0:49:29.70,Default,,0,0,0,,80/20 rule is a design principle
Dialogue: 0,0:49:29.98,0:49:33.08,Default,,0,0,0,,that says in essence 80 percent
Dialogue: 0,0:49:33.08,0:49:35.24,Default,,0,0,0,,of a system's effects come from
Dialogue: 0,0:49:35.24,0:49:37.40,Default,,0,0,0,,20 percent of its causes.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:38.51,0:49:40.17,Default,,0,0,0,,For an app, this might mean that
Dialogue: 0,0:49:40.17,0:49:42.61,Default,,0,0,0,,80 percent of its benefit comes
Dialogue: 0,0:49:42.61,0:49:44.59,Default,,0,0,0,,from 20 percent of the actions
Dialogue: 0,0:49:44.59,0:49:47.17,Default,,0,0,0,,that it presents, or 80 percent
Dialogue: 0,0:49:47.17,0:49:48.88,Default,,0,0,0,,of the people who use an app are
Dialogue: 0,0:49:48.88,0:49:51.35,Default,,0,0,0,,only going to use 20 percent of
Dialogue: 0,0:49:51.35,0:49:52.13,Default,,0,0,0,,its functions.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:52.95,0:49:55.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, the exact percentages are,
Dialogue: 0,0:49:55.03,0:49:56.03,Default,,0,0,0,,of course, different.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:56.33,0:49:58.09,Default,,0,0,0,,But the basic point is valid.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:58.60,0:49:59.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Not all information or
Dialogue: 0,0:49:59.96,0:50:02.02,Default,,0,0,0,,functionality are created equal.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:02.30,0:50:04.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Some is much more important than
Dialogue: 0,0:50:04.57,0:50:05.07,Default,,0,0,0,,others.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:06.19,0:50:08.76,Default,,0,0,0,,So, in order to reduce clutter,
Dialogue: 0,0:50:09.13,0:50:10.66,Default,,0,0,0,,and simplify decision-making, it
Dialogue: 0,0:50:10.66,0:50:12.26,Default,,0,0,0,,is a really good thing to use
Dialogue: 0,0:50:12.26,0:50:14.34,Default,,0,0,0,,progressive disclosure to hide
Dialogue: 0,0:50:14.34,0:50:15.83,Default,,0,0,0,,things of lesser importance.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:16.95,0:50:18.55,Default,,0,0,0,,In other words, if your app is
Dialogue: 0,0:50:18.55,0:50:21.04,Default,,0,0,0,,complex, it is okay to make the
Dialogue: 0,0:50:21.04,0:50:22.76,Default,,0,0,0,,most useful 20 percent of
Dialogue: 0,0:50:22.76,0:50:25.19,Default,,0,0,0,,functions easier to find by
Dialogue: 0,0:50:25.19,0:50:27.06,Default,,0,0,0,,hiding the other 80 percent.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:28.10,0:50:29.95,Default,,0,0,0,,A classic example of this is the
Dialogue: 0,0:50:29.95,0:50:30.74,Default,,0,0,0,,print dialogue.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:31.35,0:50:33.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Most of the time, people only
Dialogue: 0,0:50:33.11,0:50:35.15,Default,,0,0,0,,care about the basics, which
Dialogue: 0,0:50:35.15,0:50:36.59,Default,,0,0,0,,printer they're printing to, how
Dialogue: 0,0:50:36.59,0:50:38.19,Default,,0,0,0,,many copies, what the range of
Dialogue: 0,0:50:38.22,0:50:39.02,Default,,0,0,0,,pages are.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:39.81,0:50:41.92,Default,,0,0,0,,These are way less than 20
Dialogue: 0,0:50:41.92,0:50:42.92,Default,,0,0,0,,percent of the functions
Dialogue: 0,0:50:42.92,0:50:44.84,Default,,0,0,0,,available, and it is what people
Dialogue: 0,0:50:44.84,0:50:47.10,Default,,0,0,0,,want way more than 80 percent of
Dialogue: 0,0:50:47.10,0:50:47.55,Default,,0,0,0,,the time.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:48.52,0:50:50.31,Default,,0,0,0,,When more control is needed, a
Dialogue: 0,0:50:50.31,0:50:51.94,Default,,0,0,0,,bunch of options are just one
Dialogue: 0,0:50:51.94,0:50:52.49,Default,,0,0,0,,click away.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:52.96,0:50:55.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Not only does progressive
Dialogue: 0,0:50:55.04,0:50:56.69,Default,,0,0,0,,disclosure reduce visual
Dialogue: 0,0:50:56.69,0:50:58.87,Default,,0,0,0,,clutter, and make printing less
Dialogue: 0,0:50:58.91,0:51:01.30,Default,,0,0,0,,difficult, it also lowers the
Dialogue: 0,0:51:01.30,0:51:02.56,Default,,0,0,0,,likelihood of people getting
Dialogue: 0,0:51:02.56,0:51:04.75,Default,,0,0,0,,confused and changing a setting
Dialogue: 0,0:51:04.75,0:51:05.48,Default,,0,0,0,,that they don't really
Dialogue: 0,0:51:05.48,0:51:06.20,Default,,0,0,0,,understand.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:07.22,0:51:08.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Most of us have experienced
Dialogue: 0,0:51:08.71,0:51:10.43,Default,,0,0,0,,receiving this call from a
Dialogue: 0,0:51:10.43,0:51:12.08,Default,,0,0,0,,parent, or a family member, or a
Dialogue: 0,0:51:12.08,0:51:14.32,Default,,0,0,0,,friend, who is kind of freaking
Dialogue: 0,0:51:14.32,0:51:15.93,Default,,0,0,0,,out because their computer is
Dialogue: 0,0:51:15.93,0:51:17.56,Default,,0,0,0,,not working properly, and they
Dialogue: 0,0:51:17.56,0:51:18.62,Default,,0,0,0,,changed something, and they
Dialogue: 0,0:51:18.62,0:51:19.78,Default,,0,0,0,,don't really know what they did.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:20.58,0:51:22.65,Default,,0,0,0,,This is why progressive
Dialogue: 0,0:51:22.65,0:51:24.91,Default,,0,0,0,,disclosure is your best friend.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:25.86,0:51:27.39,Default,,0,0,0,,By keeping things simple for
Dialogue: 0,0:51:27.39,0:51:29.78,Default,,0,0,0,,novices, they are less likely to
Dialogue: 0,0:51:29.78,0:51:31.76,Default,,0,0,0,,feel intimidated, overwhelmed,
Dialogue: 0,0:51:32.11,0:51:33.47,Default,,0,0,0,,or get themselves into trouble,
Dialogue: 0,0:51:34.00,0:51:35.43,Default,,0,0,0,,while more experienced users can
Dialogue: 0,0:51:35.43,0:51:37.22,Default,,0,0,0,,quickly reveal the options and
Dialogue: 0,0:51:37.22,0:51:39.52,Default,,0,0,0,,actions that they require, that
Dialogue: 0,0:51:39.94,0:51:41.22,Default,,0,0,0,,they understand, and that they
Dialogue: 0,0:51:41.22,0:51:42.51,Default,,0,0,0,,are capable of using.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:43.77,0:51:47.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay. Anyhow, in case you were
Dialogue: 0,0:51:47.40,0:51:49.11,Default,,0,0,0,,wondering, the cheeseburger and
Dialogue: 0,0:51:49.11,0:51:50.55,Default,,0,0,0,,onion rings were delicious,
Dialogue: 0,0:51:51.05,0:51:52.26,Default,,0,0,0,,thank you very much for asking.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:53.34,0:51:55.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay, so it is time for us to
Dialogue: 0,0:51:55.69,0:51:56.41,Default,,0,0,0,,get some sleep.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:56.41,0:51:58.05,Default,,0,0,0,,We will be getting up early
Dialogue: 0,0:51:58.05,0:51:59.14,Default,,0,0,0,,tomorrow, and we are going to be
Dialogue: 0,0:51:59.14,0:52:01.49,Default,,0,0,0,,doing some snorkeling, so guys,
Dialogue: 0,0:52:01.49,0:52:01.91,Default,,0,0,0,,rest up.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:02.99,0:52:04.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay, did everyone sleep well?
Dialogue: 0,0:52:05.40,0:52:06.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Was your room comfortable?
Dialogue: 0,0:52:06.90,0:52:08.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Were you able to turn on your
Dialogue: 0,0:52:08.13,0:52:09.31,Default,,0,0,0,,lights successfully?
Dialogue: 0,0:52:09.64,0:52:11.09,Default,,0,0,0,,How is that Morty faucet?
Dialogue: 0,0:52:11.09,0:52:12.41,Default,,0,0,0,,That was pretty weird, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:52:13.05,0:52:14.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay, enough small talk.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:14.21,0:52:15.87,Default,,0,0,0,,It is time for us to go see some
Dialogue: 0,0:52:15.87,0:52:16.30,Default,,0,0,0,,fish.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:16.80,0:52:18.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, after another highly
Dialogue: 0,0:52:18.16,0:52:20.04,Default,,0,0,0,,successful car ride, we get to
Dialogue: 0,0:52:20.04,0:52:21.81,Default,,0,0,0,,the beach, and you put on your
Dialogue: 0,0:52:21.81,0:52:22.86,Default,,0,0,0,,goggles, and you put on your
Dialogue: 0,0:52:22.92,0:52:24.62,Default,,0,0,0,,flippers, you adjust your
Dialogue: 0,0:52:24.62,0:52:26.70,Default,,0,0,0,,snorkel just so, and you get
Dialogue: 0,0:52:26.70,0:52:27.79,Default,,0,0,0,,into the water.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:27.79,0:52:29.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, there are some tropical
Dialogue: 0,0:52:29.53,0:52:30.24,Default,,0,0,0,,fish.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:30.72,0:52:32.57,Default,,0,0,0,,There is a blowfish.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:33.05,0:52:35.10,Default,,0,0,0,,There is a school of tuna fish.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:35.91,0:52:38.40,Default,,0,0,0,,There is a giant squid, for some
Dialogue: 0,0:52:38.40,0:52:40.61,Default,,0,0,0,,reason, because I had the emoji
Dialogue: 0,0:52:40.61,0:52:41.80,Default,,0,0,0,,[laughter].
Dialogue: 0,0:52:41.80,0:52:44.76,Default,,0,0,0,,It is a magical underwater
Dialogue: 0,0:52:44.76,0:52:45.49,Default,,0,0,0,,wonderland.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:46.52,0:52:49.67,Default,,0,0,0,,It is so utterly beautiful, but
Dialogue: 0,0:52:49.67,0:52:50.10,Default,,0,0,0,,why?
Dialogue: 0,0:52:51.51,0:52:53.47,Default,,0,0,0,,This brings us to our very last
Dialogue: 0,0:52:53.50,0:52:54.39,Default,,0,0,0,,design principle.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:55.15,0:52:58.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Symmetry. Symmetry is a concept
Dialogue: 0,0:52:58.05,0:52:59.53,Default,,0,0,0,,that we are all deeply familiar
Dialogue: 0,0:52:59.53,0:53:01.26,Default,,0,0,0,,with, and when we think about
Dialogue: 0,0:53:01.26,0:53:02.57,Default,,0,0,0,,symmetry, we typically think
Dialogue: 0,0:53:02.57,0:53:04.76,Default,,0,0,0,,about reflectional or bilateral
Dialogue: 0,0:53:04.83,0:53:05.30,Default,,0,0,0,,symmetry.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:05.98,0:53:06.93,Default,,0,0,0,,But there is more.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:07.66,0:53:09.44,Default,,0,0,0,,There is also radial, and
Dialogue: 0,0:53:09.44,0:53:10.63,Default,,0,0,0,,rotational symmetry.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:11.54,0:53:13.55,Default,,0,0,0,,And there is also translational
Dialogue: 0,0:53:13.65,0:53:14.11,Default,,0,0,0,,symmetry.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:16.10,0:53:17.94,Default,,0,0,0,,These three types of symmetry
Dialogue: 0,0:53:18.37,0:53:19.66,Default,,0,0,0,,are ubiquitous in nature.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:20.21,0:53:21.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Symmetrical forms are efficient
Dialogue: 0,0:53:21.97,0:53:23.83,Default,,0,0,0,,forms, and we tend to associate
Dialogue: 0,0:53:23.83,0:53:25.19,Default,,0,0,0,,them with good health, with
Dialogue: 0,0:53:25.19,0:53:27.03,Default,,0,0,0,,stability, balance, and
Dialogue: 0,0:53:27.03,0:53:27.85,Default,,0,0,0,,orderliness.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:28.46,0:53:29.97,Default,,0,0,0,,And we consider them to be
Dialogue: 0,0:53:29.97,0:53:32.14,Default,,0,0,0,,aesthetically pleasing, probably
Dialogue: 0,0:53:32.14,0:53:33.64,Default,,0,0,0,,for very good evolutionary
Dialogue: 0,0:53:33.64,0:53:34.29,Default,,0,0,0,,reasons.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:35.21,0:53:37.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Symmetrical elements, even if
Dialogue: 0,0:53:37.02,0:53:38.15,Default,,0,0,0,,they are not physically
Dialogue: 0,0:53:38.15,0:53:39.88,Default,,0,0,0,,connected to each other, are
Dialogue: 0,0:53:39.88,0:53:41.73,Default,,0,0,0,,perceived as though they are.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:42.51,0:53:44.78,Default,,0,0,0,,So when we see these two facing
Dialogue: 0,0:53:44.78,0:53:47.00,Default,,0,0,0,,square brackets, our mind
Dialogue: 0,0:53:47.00,0:53:48.80,Default,,0,0,0,,unconsciously integrates them
Dialogue: 0,0:53:49.19,0:53:51.70,Default,,0,0,0,,into one coherent object.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:52.84,0:53:54.53,Default,,0,0,0,,And as you swim around, you'll
Dialogue: 0,0:53:54.53,0:53:56.18,Default,,0,0,0,,find all three forms of
Dialogue: 0,0:53:56.18,0:53:56.75,Default,,0,0,0,,symmetry.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:57.91,0:54:00.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Bilateral symmetry, rotational
Dialogue: 0,0:54:00.99,0:54:03.68,Default,,0,0,0,,symmetry, and translational
Dialogue: 0,0:54:03.68,0:54:04.15,Default,,0,0,0,,symmetry.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:05.24,0:54:07.03,Default,,0,0,0,,As a matter of fact, just about
Dialogue: 0,0:54:07.03,0:54:08.53,Default,,0,0,0,,every type of plant or animal,
Dialogue: 0,0:54:08.53,0:54:11.17,Default,,0,0,0,,both in the sea, in the water,
Dialogue: 0,0:54:11.17,0:54:12.78,Default,,0,0,0,,on land, in the air,
Dialogue: 0,0:54:13.06,0:54:14.94,Default,,0,0,0,,demonstrates one or more types
Dialogue: 0,0:54:14.98,0:54:15.70,Default,,0,0,0,,of symmetry.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:16.20,0:54:18.22,Default,,0,0,0,,And most human-made objects do
Dialogue: 0,0:54:18.22,0:54:18.75,Default,,0,0,0,,as well.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:19.54,0:54:21.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Light switches are symmetrical
Dialogue: 0,0:54:21.40,0:54:23.43,Default,,0,0,0,,across both the horizontal and
Dialogue: 0,0:54:23.43,0:54:24.33,Default,,0,0,0,,vertical axes.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:25.27,0:54:27.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Faucets are symmetrical.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:27.76,0:54:29.51,Default,,0,0,0,,And cars are symmetrical.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:29.51,0:54:31.64,Default,,0,0,0,,[Laughs] Now there is obviously
Dialogue: 0,0:54:31.64,0:54:34.41,Default,,0,0,0,,some very practical functional
Dialogue: 0,0:54:34.41,0:54:36.63,Default,,0,0,0,,reasons why cars are
Dialogue: 0,0:54:36.63,0:54:37.34,Default,,0,0,0,,symmetrical.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:38.00,0:54:40.85,Default,,0,0,0,,I mean, there is a very rational
Dialogue: 0,0:54:40.85,0:54:42.13,Default,,0,0,0,,reason why you don't want to get
Dialogue: 0,0:54:42.13,0:54:44.07,Default,,0,0,0,,into that car.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:44.26,0:54:47.39,Default,,0,0,0,,But there are clearly aesthetic
Dialogue: 0,0:54:47.39,0:54:48.33,Default,,0,0,0,,benefits as well.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:49.12,0:54:51.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Attractive interfaces tend to
Dialogue: 0,0:54:51.04,0:54:52.45,Default,,0,0,0,,demonstrate a mixture of
Dialogue: 0,0:54:52.45,0:54:54.24,Default,,0,0,0,,reflectional and translational
Dialogue: 0,0:54:54.24,0:54:54.79,Default,,0,0,0,,symmetry.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:55.25,0:54:56.72,Default,,0,0,0,,In the Weather app, reflectional
Dialogue: 0,0:54:56.72,0:54:58.11,Default,,0,0,0,,symmetry provides a sense of
Dialogue: 0,0:54:58.17,0:54:58.72,Default,,0,0,0,,balance.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:59.29,0:55:01.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Key elements are centered along
Dialogue: 0,0:55:01.12,0:55:03.53,Default,,0,0,0,,a median line, while almost all
Dialogue: 0,0:55:03.53,0:55:04.53,Default,,0,0,0,,of the other elements are
Dialogue: 0,0:55:04.53,0:55:05.86,Default,,0,0,0,,counter-balanced with each
Dialogue: 0,0:55:05.86,0:55:06.12,Default,,0,0,0,,other.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:07.23,0:55:08.31,Default,,0,0,0,,This is a pattern which is
Dialogue: 0,0:55:08.31,0:55:10.22,Default,,0,0,0,,reflected in apps like the
Dialogue: 0,0:55:10.22,0:55:14.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Camera app, the Clock app, and
Dialogue: 0,0:55:14.25,0:55:16.50,Default,,0,0,0,,the Phone app, and many, many
Dialogue: 0,0:55:16.50,0:55:16.82,Default,,0,0,0,,more.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:18.22,0:55:20.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Translational symmetry gives an
Dialogue: 0,0:55:20.28,0:55:22.14,Default,,0,0,0,,interface a sense of structure,
Dialogue: 0,0:55:22.36,0:55:24.17,Default,,0,0,0,,and order through the repetition
Dialogue: 0,0:55:24.17,0:55:25.36,Default,,0,0,0,,of like elements.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:26.14,0:55:27.49,Default,,0,0,0,,You can see translational
Dialogue: 0,0:55:27.49,0:55:29.37,Default,,0,0,0,,symmetry in the even repetition
Dialogue: 0,0:55:29.37,0:55:31.13,Default,,0,0,0,,of cities and times in the Clock
Dialogue: 0,0:55:31.13,0:55:33.88,Default,,0,0,0,,app, or the even cadence of
Dialogue: 0,0:55:33.88,0:55:35.35,Default,,0,0,0,,locations in the Weather app.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:36.59,0:55:37.68,Default,,0,0,0,,When laying out your app's
Dialogue: 0,0:55:37.68,0:55:39.15,Default,,0,0,0,,interface, look for
Dialogue: 0,0:55:39.15,0:55:41.59,Default,,0,0,0,,opportunities to use symmetry to
Dialogue: 0,0:55:41.59,0:55:43.21,Default,,0,0,0,,provide a sense of balance and
Dialogue: 0,0:55:43.21,0:55:43.56,Default,,0,0,0,,order.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:44.61,0:55:47.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay, so, everyone, I am sorry
Dialogue: 0,0:55:47.54,0:55:48.74,Default,,0,0,0,,to be the bearer of bad news,
Dialogue: 0,0:55:48.74,0:55:50.79,Default,,0,0,0,,but it's time for us to get out
Dialogue: 0,0:55:50.79,0:55:51.31,Default,,0,0,0,,of the water.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:51.31,0:55:52.71,Default,,0,0,0,,There are a lot of you, and we
Dialogue: 0,0:55:52.71,0:55:53.82,Default,,0,0,0,,can only pay for a half day
Dialogue: 0,0:55:53.82,0:55:54.08,Default,,0,0,0,,trip.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:54.75,0:55:56.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Also, I don't know if you saw,
Dialogue: 0,0:55:56.21,0:55:57.50,Default,,0,0,0,,there was a shark in the water,
Dialogue: 0,0:55:57.50,0:55:58.63,Default,,0,0,0,,and I am really starting to
Dialogue: 0,0:55:58.63,0:55:59.09,Default,,0,0,0,,freak out.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:59.58,0:56:03.50,Default,,0,0,0,,So we return back to sunny San
Dialogue: 0,0:56:03.50,0:56:03.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Jose.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:04.60,0:56:06.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, the snorkeling here is not
Dialogue: 0,0:56:06.19,0:56:07.61,Default,,0,0,0,,quite as beautiful as Hawaii,
Dialogue: 0,0:56:07.61,0:56:09.51,Default,,0,0,0,,and I strongly urge you not to
Dialogue: 0,0:56:09.51,0:56:10.25,Default,,0,0,0,,go into the bay.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:10.74,0:56:12.10,Default,,0,0,0,,But our technical and design
Dialogue: 0,0:56:12.10,0:56:14.52,Default,,0,0,0,,content is way better, so it's a
Dialogue: 0,0:56:14.52,0:56:14.97,Default,,0,0,0,,win-win.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:15.85,0:56:17.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, the design principles that
Dialogue: 0,0:56:17.23,0:56:18.84,Default,,0,0,0,,we explored today express
Dialogue: 0,0:56:18.92,0:56:21.13,Default,,0,0,0,,fundamental truths about human
Dialogue: 0,0:56:21.13,0:56:22.62,Default,,0,0,0,,perception and cognition.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:23.52,0:56:25.47,Default,,0,0,0,,They are simple, but powerful
Dialogue: 0,0:56:25.47,0:56:27.54,Default,,0,0,0,,reminders about the true nature
Dialogue: 0,0:56:27.85,0:56:29.38,Default,,0,0,0,,and purpose of design.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:30.21,0:56:31.81,Default,,0,0,0,,They provide a framework for
Dialogue: 0,0:56:31.81,0:56:33.80,Default,,0,0,0,,understanding, and a language
Dialogue: 0,0:56:33.88,0:56:36.14,Default,,0,0,0,,for articulating a design's
Dialogue: 0,0:56:36.23,0:56:38.49,Default,,0,0,0,,strengths and its shortcomings.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:39.45,0:56:41.34,Default,,0,0,0,,My hope is that in sharing these
Dialogue: 0,0:56:41.34,0:56:42.81,Default,,0,0,0,,principles with you today, you
Dialogue: 0,0:56:43.75,0:56:45.50,Default,,0,0,0,,will come away with a clear
Dialogue: 0,0:56:45.50,0:56:48.26,Default,,0,0,0,,sense of how your app's designs
Dialogue: 0,0:56:48.74,0:56:50.97,Default,,0,0,0,,can help to fulfill those basic
Dialogue: 0,0:56:50.97,0:56:53.07,Default,,0,0,0,,needs that we all share.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:53.82,0:56:55.36,Default,,0,0,0,,The need to feel safe.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:55.71,0:56:57.26,Default,,0,0,0,,The need to understand.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:57.53,0:56:59.38,Default,,0,0,0,,The need to achieve our goals,
Dialogue: 0,0:56:59.69,0:57:01.31,Default,,0,0,0,,and the need to experience
Dialogue: 0,0:57:01.37,0:57:02.95,Default,,0,0,0,,beauty and joy.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:04.29,0:57:05.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, to be sure, while these
Dialogue: 0,0:57:05.83,0:57:07.15,Default,,0,0,0,,principles are, in many ways,
Dialogue: 0,0:57:07.15,0:57:08.57,Default,,0,0,0,,quite simple, applying them to
Dialogue: 0,0:57:08.60,0:57:09.93,Default,,0,0,0,,your work is not.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:11.16,0:57:12.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Each of these principles could
Dialogue: 0,0:57:12.49,0:57:13.69,Default,,0,0,0,,lead you into different
Dialogue: 0,0:57:13.69,0:57:15.49,Default,,0,0,0,,directions about what you should
Dialogue: 0,0:57:15.49,0:57:17.07,Default,,0,0,0,,do with the design of your app.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:18.12,0:57:20.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Designing is so often about
Dialogue: 0,0:57:20.20,0:57:21.78,Default,,0,0,0,,resolving those differences.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:22.42,0:57:23.90,Default,,0,0,0,,This is something that the very
Dialogue: 0,0:57:23.90,0:57:25.53,Default,,0,0,0,,best designers struggle with.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:26.81,0:57:28.68,Default,,0,0,0,,It is also possible to have too
Dialogue: 0,0:57:28.68,0:57:29.57,Default,,0,0,0,,much of a good thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:29.97,0:57:31.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Too much feedback is annoying.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:31.42,0:57:32.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Too much visibility is
Dialogue: 0,0:57:32.94,0:57:33.56,Default,,0,0,0,,distracting.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:33.84,0:57:35.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Too much progressive disclosure
Dialogue: 0,0:57:35.79,0:57:37.60,Default,,0,0,0,,can make work flows inefficient.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:38.34,0:57:39.87,Default,,0,0,0,,So you have to be measured in
Dialogue: 0,0:57:39.87,0:57:41.85,Default,,0,0,0,,your approach, and exercise
Dialogue: 0,0:57:41.94,0:57:43.65,Default,,0,0,0,,judgment and discretion.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:44.70,0:57:46.01,Default,,0,0,0,,And the relevance of each
Dialogue: 0,0:57:46.01,0:57:48.10,Default,,0,0,0,,principle can vary depending on
Dialogue: 0,0:57:48.10,0:57:49.60,Default,,0,0,0,,what kind of app you're making.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:50.61,0:57:52.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Platform. Screen size.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:52.78,0:57:55.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Use case. The experience level
Dialogue: 0,0:57:55.56,0:57:56.36,Default,,0,0,0,,of the people who you are
Dialogue: 0,0:57:56.36,0:57:57.26,Default,,0,0,0,,designing for.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:57.89,0:57:59.82,Default,,0,0,0,,These factors and more should
Dialogue: 0,0:57:59.82,0:58:01.74,Default,,0,0,0,,influence what principles are
Dialogue: 0,0:58:01.74,0:58:03.62,Default,,0,0,0,,most relevant at any given
Dialogue: 0,0:58:03.62,0:58:03.99,Default,,0,0,0,,moment.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:05.08,0:58:06.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Working through this can be
Dialogue: 0,0:58:06.64,0:58:07.27,Default,,0,0,0,,challenging.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:08.00,0:58:09.28,Default,,0,0,0,,No one said that designing is
Dialogue: 0,0:58:09.28,0:58:11.97,Default,,0,0,0,,easy, but I do not want you to
Dialogue: 0,0:58:11.97,0:58:12.99,Default,,0,0,0,,be discouraged.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:13.71,0:58:15.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Designing is a lot easier when
Dialogue: 0,0:58:15.58,0:58:17.93,Default,,0,0,0,,you understand the fundamentals.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:18.67,0:58:20.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Let these principles be your
Dialogue: 0,0:58:20.46,0:58:21.42,Default,,0,0,0,,North Star.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:22.11,0:58:23.39,Default,,0,0,0,,They will guide you toward
Dialogue: 0,0:58:23.39,0:58:25.95,Default,,0,0,0,,making apps that better serve
Dialogue: 0,0:58:26.45,0:58:28.00,Default,,0,0,0,,the human beings that you are
Dialogue: 0,0:58:28.00,0:58:28.88,Default,,0,0,0,,designing for.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:29.78,0:58:31.40,Default,,0,0,0,,And that is the thing that
Dialogue: 0,0:58:31.40,0:58:32.37,Default,,0,0,0,,matters most.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:33.48,0:58:35.41,Default,,0,0,0,,And in turn, the people that you
Dialogue: 0,0:58:35.41,0:58:36.52,Default,,0,0,0,,are designing for will
Dialogue: 0,0:58:36.52,0:58:39.37,Default,,0,0,0,,recognize, on some level, all of
Dialogue: 0,0:58:39.37,0:58:40.85,Default,,0,0,0,,the hard work that you have
Dialogue: 0,0:58:40.85,0:58:41.46,Default,,0,0,0,,invested.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:42.05,0:58:43.31,Default,,0,0,0,,They will appreciate the
Dialogue: 0,0:58:43.45,0:58:46.24,Default,,0,0,0,,thoughtfulness and care, and
Dialogue: 0,0:58:46.59,0:58:49.22,Default,,0,0,0,,they will sense the humanity of
Dialogue: 0,0:58:49.34,0:58:51.53,Default,,0,0,0,,the people who made it.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:52.58,0:58:55.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay, so for more information,
Dialogue: 0,0:58:55.33,0:58:56.26,Default,,0,0,0,,check out this URL.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:56.79,0:58:58.97,Default,,0,0,0,,And, I want to highlight how
Dialogue: 0,0:58:58.97,0:59:00.66,Default,,0,0,0,,many amazing design sessions we
Dialogue: 0,0:59:00.66,0:59:01.42,Default,,0,0,0,,have for you this week.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:01.83,0:59:03.95,Default,,0,0,0,,We actually have eight design
Dialogue: 0,0:59:03.95,0:59:06.25,Default,,0,0,0,,sessions, which is more than we
Dialogue: 0,0:59:06.25,0:59:07.19,Default,,0,0,0,,have ever done before.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:07.19,0:59:08.56,Default,,0,0,0,,We have three sessions that have
Dialogue: 0,0:59:08.65,0:59:10.99,Default,,0,0,0,,five mini sessions in them each.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:10.99,0:59:12.26,Default,,0,0,0,,There is a lot of fantastic
Dialogue: 0,0:59:12.26,0:59:12.74,Default,,0,0,0,,content.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:13.18,0:59:14.47,Default,,0,0,0,,In particular, I want to
Dialogue: 0,0:59:14.47,0:59:16.29,Default,,0,0,0,,highlight a couple of sessions.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:16.78,0:59:18.43,Default,,0,0,0,,One is called Designing Sound.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:18.46,0:59:21.22,Default,,0,0,0,,It is being given by the person
Dialogue: 0,0:59:21.22,0:59:22.74,Default,,0,0,0,,who makes basically all the
Dialogue: 0,0:59:22.74,0:59:24.29,Default,,0,0,0,,sounds that are on your devices.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:24.60,0:59:26.38,Default,,0,0,0,,It is nothing, like nothing we
Dialogue: 0,0:59:26.38,0:59:27.26,Default,,0,0,0,,have ever done before.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:27.58,0:59:28.56,Default,,0,0,0,,It is really fantastic.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:28.56,0:59:29.50,Default,,0,0,0,,It is this afternoon.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:30.05,0:59:31.66,Default,,0,0,0,,And you should go check out
Dialogue: 0,0:59:31.69,0:59:33.55,Default,,0,0,0,,tomorrow, a presentation called
Dialogue: 0,0:59:33.55,0:59:35.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Designing Across Platforms,
Dialogue: 0,0:59:35.67,0:59:37.27,Default,,0,0,0,,which helps to solve really
Dialogue: 0,0:59:37.27,0:59:39.27,Default,,0,0,0,,tricky issues about how to adapt
Dialogue: 0,0:59:39.27,0:59:41.10,Default,,0,0,0,,your app to different platforms.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:41.10,0:59:42.59,Default,,0,0,0,,It is really awesome.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:43.36,0:59:44.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay, you guys, it has really
Dialogue: 0,0:59:44.96,0:59:46.54,Default,,0,0,0,,been an honor and my pleasure to
Dialogue: 0,0:59:46.54,0:59:47.30,Default,,0,0,0,,talk with you today.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:47.61,0:59:48.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you so much.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:49.52,0:59:55.17,Default,,0,0,0,,[ Applause ]
